<title>Apr_1993: The $100 Million Question</title>
<h1>The $100 Million Question</h1>
Steven Timm (<i>st0o+@andrew.cmu.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Wed, 21 Apr 1993 00:33:09 -0400 (EDT)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#339">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#339">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#339">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#339">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0340.html">Healy, Tammy R: "Re: Jack in the Box Lies"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0338.html">Ruben Gonzalez: "Re: Background on Ruben's post"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
<li> <b>Next in thread:</b> <a href="0351.html">Michael Merginio: "Re: The $100 Million Question"</a>
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
[This is a hypothetical situation, but it's based on real life, see below  SCT]<br>
Suppose you are the president of a small SDA college in the Southern US.<br>
Finances are typically tight.  Suddenly one day you receive a call from <br>
the attorneys of a deceased church member.  This member, well-known to you,<br>
has offered to leave a sum of $100 million to your college if a few<br>
conditions are met.<br>
<p>
1)  All college faculty must sign an oath of allegiance to a long list<br>
of "historically correct" conservative SDA teachings, and abandon their<br>
membership in the Association of Adventist Forums.<br>
<p>
2)  All theology books by liberal SDA's and non-SDA's must be removed <br>
from the library.<br>
<p>
3)  Evolution is not to be mentioned even as theory in any science class.<br>
Further, you must hire Dr. Bob Gentry and fund his research.<br>
<p>
4)  No female students will be allowed to enter the theology program<br>
<p>
5)  Your college press must publish and promote his book, particularly<br>
it should be carried by all the Adventist Book Centers.  His book deals with <br>
the issues above and more.<br>
<p>
6)  Colin Standish of Hartland Institute should be hired as Vice<br>
President for Academic Administration<br>
<p>
If any of the six conditions are not met, the money will go to Hartland <br>
Institute instead.<br>
<p>
You contact your Board of Trustees and the General Conference leadership, <br>
they urge you to take the offer.  What do you do?<br>
<p>
[Note, the Church of Jesus Christ, Scientist  (Christian Science), is <br>
undergoing a similar situation as we speak, and they are careening<br>
towards schism because of it.  The lure of money from tax-exempt bonds<br>
led Jerry <br>
Falwell to declare his Liberty University a "non-religious school".  <br>
Let's not say it can't happen here.  SCT]<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
