Regarding the statement "He had never been separated from His father, we<br>
often are."<br>
<p>
Yes, we all agree with that. The difference between positions lies in the<br>
fact that some would say that sin is separation from the father, and some<br>
would not.<br>
<p>
Regarding Priebe's article, in my view he used "rather than" a few too many<br>
times. There aren't as many "mutual exclusives" there as he claims. Even as<br>
far down the tree as character perfection, all can aim for it and see it as<br>
valuable, it's just that some label it as sinlessness and some don't.<br>
<p>
Tony<br>
