<i>&gt; Suppose you are the president of a small SDA college in the Southern US.</i><br>
<i>&gt; Finances are typically tight.  Suddenly one day you receive a call from </i><br>
<i>&gt; the attorneys of a deceased church member.  This member, well-known to you,</i><br>
<i>&gt; has offered to leave a sum of $100 million to your college if a few</i><br>
<i>&gt; conditions are met.</i><br>
<p>
The money should not be accepted.<br>
Freedom of choice (in this case regarding institutional policy-making)<br>
is worth far more than any amount of money.<br>
