<title>Apr_1993: Re: The $100 Million Question</title>
<h1>Re: The $100 Million Question</h1>
Michael Merginio (<i>merginim@susan.cs.andrews.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Wed, 21 Apr 1993 10:55:59 -0400 (EDT)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#351">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#351">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#351">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#351">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0352.html">Stephen Alan Turk: "Re: The $100 Million Question"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0350.html">Steve Hix: "Re: Vitamin B12 in Soysauce"</a>
<li> <b>In reply to:</b> <a href="0339.html">Steven Timm: "The $100 Million Question"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
<li> <b>Next in thread:</b> <a href="0388.html">Fred Christiansen: "Re: The $100 Million Question"</a>
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
Steve,<br>
<p>
If I were that president,  I know that I would have to turn it down and<br>
let the Heartland Institute have the money.  Any kind of stipulation which<br>
would essentially discourage any "opposing" thought would not be the kind<br>
of institution I would allow to be under my control.  A college/university<br>
is supposed to be a place where alternate thought is not only expected,<br>
but encouraged.  The college experience is to be one where a person should<br>
be allowed to find the true being within oneself.<br>
<p>
I could never forgive myself for being a part of a plot to "eliminate" the<br>
"undesireable teachings" of an ultra-conservative.  I could not do it if<br>
the person were on the other side of the coin either.  A college must be<br>
able to encourage free thought I feel that this would seriously hamper<br>
that ability.<br>
<p>
<pre>
--
Wishing You all the Best in Life,
Michael B. Merginio
merginim@andrews.edu
<p>
James White Library, Berrien Springs, MI 49104-1300, (616) 471-6344
=====================================================================
I believe that in our world, this is one rule that everyone
	should follow, and that is - TELL IT LIKE IT IS!!!!!
	The truth may hurt, but lies, or witholding the truth 
	makes it hurt even more.    --M.B. Merginio 
Disclaimer--Only blame ME for the Opinions Expressed in this message.
=====================================================================
</pre>
