Hi,<br>
somebody on the net asked where to find the <br>
text about stars on the crown.  Well, thanks to my<br>
mom I got the source (may not satisfy all my curiosity though).<br>
Try looking at Early writings by E.G.White <br>
I happened to be reading it from Korean Translations<br>
so I can't give you the page numbers, but it's the first<br>
chapter (First Vision I should say) pg 17 in Korean One.<br>
So it should be around there I guess. (hopefully someone will look up<br>
and post correct pg number).<br>
It says something like<br>
" Some were wearing very shiny crowns, some had stars on the crown<br>
and it looked heavy.  Some cronw had few stars.  but all seemed to be<br>
satisfied by what they had." <br>
