<!-- body="start" -->
Could it be possible that the reason the plants grew away from the rock<br>
music is because of the sheer volume at which rock music is typically<br>
played?<br>
<p>
Through my almost eighteen year walk with Christ, I have often heard<br>
many more mature Christians judge something they did not like as being<br>
ungodly.  After all, if they liked it, and they have the mind of Christ,<br>
then it must be good.  conversely, if they don't like something, then it<br>
must be of satanic origin.<br>
<p>
I have heard such things regarding Christian rock music.  If an elder<br>
Christian doesn't like it, then it must be of satanic origin.  <br>
<p>
Former President George Bush claimed to be a Christian.  He hated<br>
brocolli.  Therefore, I guess broccoli is of satanic origin.  <br>
<p>
Hope this helps to muddy the waters.<br>
<p>
Ray the kop<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
