Well gang, I've looked up soy sauce in my handy dandy Pennington book<br>
on Food Values and there ain't any B-12 in soy sauce!  Regardless of<br>
whether the soy sauce is made with hydrolyzed vegetable protein, with<br>
soy and wheat (shoyu), or soy only (tamari), a quarter (1/4) cup has<br>
0.0 mcg of b-12.  So don't count on Chinese food making up your b-12<br>
requirement...<br>
<p>
Lola<br>
Aagaard@Morekypr<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
