Well, I'm rather surprised that principle took the precedence over<br>
financial utopia for you hypothetical administrators.  But to show you<br>
how reasonable<br>
I really am, I'll give you another chance.<br>
<p>
This time no oaths of allegiance to anyone, no censorship, nothing like that.<br>
The deal is as follows:  We donate 5 million dollars to the school, to <br>
be used for the construction of a new theology building and the funding of <br>
3 endowed chairs in theology.  All we ask is that the professors appointed<br>
to those chairs pass our standards for approval (as long as they are members<br>
in good standing of the Adventist Theological Society it should be OK).<br>
<p>
Now what do you say?<br>
<p>
Steve Timm<br>
