<title>Apr_1993: Re: Priebe, Ford, Larson, and college</title>
<h1>Re: Priebe, Ford, Larson, and college</h1>
Noe Torres | ECISD (<i>noe@tenet.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Tue, 27 Apr 1993 07:51:07 -0500 (CDT)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#406">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#406">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#406">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#406">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0407.html">PHTH1@cc.newcastle.edu.au: "Church clothes"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0405.html">Bill Oblitey: "Re: The $5 million dollar question"</a>
<li> <b>In reply to:</b> <a href="0393.html">AAGAARD%morekypr.BITNET@bitnet.cc.cmu.edu: "Priebe, Ford, Larson, and college"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
On 26 Apr 1993 AAGAARD@morekypr.bitnet wrote:<br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; So what, you say?  Well, so what indeed.  I just wanted to interject the</i><br>
<i>&gt; human dimension a bit here, because some of these men have been</i><br>
<i>&gt; thoroughly blasted for their various doctrinal positions, and we should</i><br>
<i>&gt; remember that they are indeed human and that we might be able to disagree</i><br>
<i>&gt; with them without becoming disagreeable.</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
I'll even go farther and say that we NEED men like Priebe, Ford, and<br>
Larson to express their opinions, thus giving us a chance to dig deeply<br>
into the Word of God and mine its treasures for ourselves.  If they are<br>
earnest searchers of God's Word, yielding to God's Spirit, and willing to<br>
be open-minded and not accusatory or critical of those who take different<br>
theological positions, men like these are very much to be coveted by the<br>
church for the insight, thought and study that they inspire in all of us. <br>
I agree with Lola one-hundred-percent.<br>
<p>
I would also remind Lola that we who take different viewpoints have as<br>
much right to express ourselves as do the men whose theological positions<br>
we are discussing.  I personally don't think anyone has been "blasted" on<br>
this forum; I believe there has been open, honest, and fruitful debate<br>
concerning the issues raised by some of these men.  "Blasted" is an<br>
inappropriate adjective here.<br>
<p>
The danger comes when teachers of God's Word become purposely critical,<br>
accusatory, denunciatory -- dredging up negativity to heap upon God's<br>
Advent people.  I'm not necessarily saying that Priebe, Ford, and/or<br>
Larson specifically have done this; I'm just noting that when it happens,<br>
the offending individuals are running a great risk spiritually.<br>
<p>
NOE.<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
