Well now I know why our organists love that modulation for the last verse<br>
of the hymns. The only problem is, our organist tends to also play a different<br>
harmonic arrangement for the last verse. This leaves me in a vile predicament.<br>
I can't sing high enough to modulate up a note, and I can't sing the bass part<br>
because it has been significantly altered! I love the modulations and also<br>
the innovative arrangements, but I also like to sing the hymns.<br>
<p>
So to all your organists out there - if you are planning to change key then<br>
please START LOWER!!! Otherwise I can see I will need to invest in some new<br>
pants for church, a couple of sizes smaller.  :-O<br>
<p>
Before I conclude, let me express my thanks to all those who share their<br>
talents in worship. Especially musicians, I particularly appreciate your<br>
contributions.<br>
<p>
btw, I take it I should have said "potted plants"? What do you guys call<br>
plants in pots??<br>
<p>
Tony<br>
