<title>Apr_1993: Earthquake Predictions</title>
<h1>Earthquake Predictions</h1>
Bruce Holm (<i>bruceh@wv.mentorg.com</i>)<br>
<i>Wed, 28 Apr 93 10:41:47 -0700</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#423">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#423">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#423">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#423">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0424.html">Bruce Holm: "What Is The "Will of God"?"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0422.html">Steven Timm: "Re: Stars in My Crown"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
<li> <b>Next in thread:</b> <a href="0428.html">Alan Fargusson: "Re: Earthquake Predictions"</a>
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
Just thought I would inform you on SDA net about a news event taking place here<br>
in Portland, OR (USA).  John Gunter, a member of an Assemblies of God church <br>
here in the metro area has risen up and making know via a 3 page letter he wrote<br>
a series of events that have taken place independent of each other over the past<br>
few months that indicate to him that God is planning to reign judgement on this<br>
city on May 3, 1993 in the form of a very strong earthquake.  He claims that the<br>
city is a very strong if not the strongest center for Satanism in the country<br>
and that God has indicated to him and others he has spoken with that God is going<br>
to punish the city by destroying it.  He sent this letter to 1080 churches in the<br>
Portland/Vancouver (WA) area.  It has gotten radio and TV coverage.<br>
<p>
At first this sounds far fetched.  But it has ALOT of people in the area taking<br>
this seriously.  We had a moderate quake of 5.7 on the scale on March 25.  He<br>
states that he had been impressed that God is going to punish the city and is<br>
going to give 40 days of warning, just like Ninevah. But he didn't know when the<br>
40 days were going to start.  Then when the March 25 quake hit, he ran to his<br>
calendar and counted...May 3 came up.  This matched identically with what another<br>
Christian pastor (a Russian)who had someone he knew in his congregation that <br>
claims to have been told by God that May 3 a powerful earthquake would strike<br>
Portland on May 3 and destroy downtown and the west hills (housing area on the <br>
west side of downtown).<br>
<p>
What is spooky is that geologists are predicting the same thing to happen (a very<br>
powerful earthquake) to hit Portland soon (between tomorrow and 100 years is the<br>
official date range) but when asked what they personally think off the camera,<br>
they say they have been told to not tell by the CIA for fear of causing panic.<br>
<p>
I could go on with details but just wanted to see what others thought.  How do<br>
you know if this message is really from God?  Would God give a warning message<br>
like this to a non-SDA?  Why not?  SDA's tend to sit on their seats when it <br>
comes to stuff like this.  He may have chosen someone who he knew would get the<br>
word out.<br>
<p>
As a side note, a friend of mine in Seattle mentioned recently that he read that<br>
a chinease prophet has predicted a major catastrophe to hit the Pacific NW of <br>
US the first week of May.  And yet another person my wife works with said he saw<br>
a psychic prediction at a new years party that stated that a major catastrophe<br>
would strike the pacific NW the first week of May and the stock market would <br>
crash shortly afterwards.<br>
<p>
Are we living in the last days or what??<br>
I don't know if this is true or not but I quess we will all know May 3.  I would<br>
like to ask...IF it does happen where did the message come from? (God or Satan)<br>
<p>
<p>
<pre>
-- 
Bruce G. Holm               503-685-1350      email:  bruceh@wv.mentorg.com
Mentor Graphics Corp.       503-685-7000
8005 SW Boeckman Rd.
Wilsonville, OR 97070-7777     Disclaimer:  Opinions expressed are my own!
</pre>
