<title>Apr_1993: Re: Original sin (and guilt)</title>
<h1>Re: Original sin (and guilt)</h1>
Sherman Cox (<i>scox@uahcs2.cs.uah.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Thu, 29 Apr 93 8:30:11 CDT</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#430">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#430">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#430">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#430">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0431.html">Dan Drazen: "Re: Stars in My Crown"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0429.html">Alan Fargusson: "Re: WWC and Internet News"</a>
<li> <b>In reply to:</b> <a href="0416.html">Steven Timm: "Original sin (and guilt)"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
<li> <b>Next in thread:</b> <a href="0432.html">Sherman Cox: "Re: Original sin (and guilt)"</a>
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
Noe wrote:<br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; Ruben's argument, if I understand it correctly, is that no guilt or sin</i><br>
<i>&gt; passes to us from the transgression at Eden -- only the "sinful nature"</i><br>
<i>&gt; (meaning, presumably, the effects of centuries of sin on the human</i><br>
<i>&gt; organism).   We begin life with a "blank slate" and actually</i><br>
<i>&gt; ***could*** bypass Christ's Atonement and accomplish our own salvation</i><br>
<i>&gt; if we tap into enough "power" (whatever that is).</i><br>
<p>
I would first say that I do not fully understand Ruben's position, but I <br>
believe it is close to mine.  I would not presume to speak for Ruben, so<br>
I will speak for my understanding.  I realize it was not asked for.<br>
<p>
The "power" comes from the life and death of Christ.  If we are separated<br>
from Christ, we are separated from the "power" which makes it impossible<br>
to keep from sinning.  It is not a true statement to say that the "power"<br>
is separate from Christ's Atonement.  It is because of the full ministry,<br>
of Christ that we are able to have such power.  Therefore we could not<br>
access the power without the ministy of Christ.  So it is not possible to <br>
bypass Christ's Atonement and tap into the power for Christs life, death,<br>
and ministry in the sanctuary above makes the power available.<br>
<p>
I understand Noe's fear of the word "power"  It could mean anything.  I<br>
agree we should define our terms.  I have used the term so I will now try<br>
to define what I mean by it.  Once again this is SHerman talking not Ruben.<br>
I believe the power to be Christ in us.  As Paul said, "I am crucified with<br>
Christ, nevertheless I live, yet not I, but Christ liveth in me."  Gal 2:20.<br>
This is imparted righteousness.  Once again, I would stress that it is not<br>
fair to say we could accomplish our own salvation by tapping into the power,<br>
the power is only available because of Christ.<br>
<p>
I should not have used fear in the above paragraph, perhaps discomfort.<br>
<p>
I believe we should look at what we all mean by salvation.  I wonder if we<br>
are using it to mean exactly the same thing.<br>
<p>
<p>
<pre>
-- 
"Keep the Faith, Baby"  --  Adam Clayton Powell, Jr
"Keep Hope Alive"       --  Jesse Jackson
"We are Saved by Hope"  --  Paul
<p>
Sherman H. Cox, II       scox@uahcs2.cs.uah.edu
</pre>
<!-- body="end" -->
