<title>Apr_1993: Re: Original sin (and guilt)</title>
<h1>Re: Original sin (and guilt)</h1>
Sherman Cox (<i>scox@uahcs2.cs.uah.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Thu, 29 Apr 93 8:56:18 CDT</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#432">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#432">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#432">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#432">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0433.html">Bill Robinson, GSLIS, 4-2148: "Thought for the day (xpost)"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0431.html">Dan Drazen: "Re: Stars in My Crown"</a>
<li> <b>In reply to:</b> <a href="0416.html">Steven Timm: "Original sin (and guilt)"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
<li> <b>Next in thread:</b> <a href="0435.html">Ruben Gonzalez: "Re: Original sin (and guilt)"</a>
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
Noe wrote:<br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; No, that battle was won by Christ nearly 2,000 years ago.  Our battle is</i><br>
<i>&gt; to choose Jesus Christ day-by-day, moment-by-moment -- to love Him and</i><br>
<i>&gt; serve Him and be faithful to Him.  That is to be the peak of our</i><br>
<i>&gt; experience.  That is to be our drive and motivation.  The obedience that</i><br>
<i>&gt; flows from such an experience is the only kind of obedience that is acceptible</i><br>
<i>&gt; to God.  If we are striving to choose not to sin, we are rendering the sullen</i><br>
<i>&gt; submission of a rebel.</i><br>
<p>
We cannot even understand the law apart from an experience with God.  You<br>
are correct, Jesus has proven that a day by day hour-by-hour connection with<br>
God can keep you from sin.  It is interesting that the only way the law<br>
can be understood and kept is coming from a love for God.  With Jesus all<br>
things are possible.  Apart from Christ we will sin and sin and sin, for<br>
we do not have the strength.<br>
<p>
<p>
<p>
<pre>
-- 
"Keep the Faith, Baby"  --  Adam Clayton Powell, Jr
"Keep Hope Alive"       --  Jesse Jackson
"We are Saved by Hope"  --  Paul
<p>
Sherman H. Cox, II       scox@uahcs2.cs.uah.edu
</pre>
