<!-- body="start" -->
<i>&gt; It's one of the most true truths I know that God answers prayer.  So would</i><br>
<i>&gt; urgent prayer for the Second Coming hasten that event or not?</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; Steve Timm</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
Steve:<br>
<p>
Since God only knows (literally) when the Second Advent will happen,<br>
it's an open question as to whether it will get here any sooner by<br>
praying for it.  We're instructed in the Lord's Prayer to ask that God's<br>
Kingdom might come, with no indication that we're hustling it along.<br>
<p>
More interesting to me is the possibility that some who may wish to<br>
hasten the Second Advent might not be too thrilled by the results.  I'm<br>
thinking of the "Lord, Lord" crowd to whom Jesus says "I never knew<br>
you."  Like the spiritual says, "Everybody talkin' 'bout Heaven ain't<br>
goin' there."  A clear case of: Be careful what you pray for, you just<br>
might get it.<br>
<p>
Daniel J. Drazen<br>
Editor, SDA Periodical Index<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
