<title>Apr_1993: Evil &amp; guilt</title>
<h1>Evil &amp; guilt</h1>
<i>PHTH1@cc.newcastle.edu.au</i><br>
<i>29 Apr 1993 11:32:47 +1000</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#426">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#426">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#426">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#426">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0427.html">Healy, Tammy R: "Re: WWC and Internet News"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0425.html">Steven Timm: "Chicago Tribune:  ADRA in Yugoslavia"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
<li> <b>Next in thread:</b> <a href="0400.html">Ruben Gonzalez: "Re: Evil &amp; guilt"</a>
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
Look at it this way folks...however you define evil, sin and guilt, Christ<br>
can save us from all three. Does it matter which _we_ classify as which,<br>
when _He_ deals with them all?<br>
<p>
Oh but that's right, that takes us back to the _when_ argument, doesn't it.<br>
<p>
:-(<br>
<p>
I suppose that's where faith comes in! We can only do our best and trust Him<br>
to get the timing right.<br>
<p>
Tony<br>
