Another issue has also surfaced here at Andrews.  We have a number of<br>
Academy students who either use or are interested in using the Internet. <br>
We also have a group of non SDA students from local high schools who come<br>
onto campus to use our facilities in Math and Sciences (including Computer<br>
Science).  Many of these individuals are "minors."  There is a lot of<br>
"adult" material available via Internet: newsgroups, pictures, "dirty"<br>
games, jokes etc.<br>
<p>
The question is this:<br>
<p>
Should these individuals be restricted in their access to these off campus<br>
resources?<br>
<p>
dan hamstra<br>
hamstra@andrews.edu<br>
