<!-- body="start" -->
Take it easy Steve.  I think caps lock does make it look like the person<br>
is shouting, and does tend to drive home a point.  <br>
<p>
In American Sign Language, the higher you make the signs, the more<br>
emphasis is placed on the message, sort of like shouting does for<br>
hearing persons.  The story goes of a deaf couple at a marraige renewal<br>
retreat, and the husband signed to the wife "You don't have to talk so<br>
high, I'm not blind, you know!"<br>
<p>
Ray the kop<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
