<title>Apr_1993: Sodom and Gomorrah</title>
<h1>Sodom and Gomorrah</h1>
Steven Timm (<i>st0o+@andrew.cmu.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Sun,  2 May 1993 12:49:44 -0400 (EDT)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#445">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#445">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#445">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#445">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0446.html">Noe Torres | ECISD: "Re: Original sin (and guilt)"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0444.html">Fred Christiansen: "Re: WWC and Internet News"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
I remember about a year ago hearing a very interesting lecture by Dr. <br>
Bill Shea that included information about several archeological sites on <br>
the east side of the Dead Sea.  These cities appear at a suitable<br>
archeological layer to have been destroyed by fire, and it is now thought<br>
that they may be the cities of Sodom and Gomorrah.<br>
<p>
Does anyone know where print documentation may be had for this discovery.<br>
I would assume in the Biblical Archaeology Review, to which I have wanted<br>
to subscribe for years but never found the subscription address.  Any <br>
SDAnet members can help us out on this?<br>
<p>
<p>
Steve Timm<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
