At Carnegie Mellon University, freedom of speech is (almost) absolute<br>
(unless you happen to be not Politically Correct).  At Fermilab, however,<br>
when we first got news here, they would only subscribe to the comp and <br>
the sci groups because they claimed the others were not in the mission <br>
of Fermilab.  The other groups still got in though, the bootleg being<br>
led by various system types.  Now we officially get them all.<br>
<p>
