<title>Mar_1992: Patty Cabrera en Espanol</title>
<h1>Patty Cabrera en Espanol</h1>
Steven Timm (<i>st0o+@andrew.cmu.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Mon,  2 Mar 1992 21:48:26 -0500 (EST)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#4">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#4">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#4">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#4">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0005.html">Steven Timm: "Iniquities, Transgressions, Sins, etc."</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0003.html">Steven Timm: "Re:  NLP"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
"Hasta Hoy" is the Spanish version of Patty Cabrera's self-titled<br>
debut album, also released on Dayspring.  I saw it in my local Christian <br>
Bookstore in the Spanish section, but didn't buy, mainly because I <br>
don't understand spanish very well, but I could make out enough to see<br>
that the songs on the album are effectively the same tunes.<br>
<p>
Has anyone heard it all the way through?  Are the translations good?<br>
This is a growing market that only a few CCM artists (Steve Green is <br>
another) are willing or able to tap.<br>
<p>
Steve Timm<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
<ul>
