<title>Mar_1992: Monopolies on truth?</title>
<h1>Monopolies on truth?</h1>
Steven Timm (<i>st0o+@andrew.cmu.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Mon,  2 Mar 1992 21:40:03 -0500 (EST)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#7">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#7">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#7">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#7">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0008.html">Steven Timm: "Re: Health Messages of 1850-1877 by nonSDA religious leaders"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0006.html">Steven Timm: "Majoring in Minors"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
<li> <b>Next in thread:</b> <a href="0010.html">Dave Buxton: "Re: Monopolies on truth?"</a>
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
When I saw Scott Mattes post about Joseph Smith, my first idea was to <br>
want to reject it.  The second was to want to go run and dig out all the <br>
dirt on Mormons I could find.   But then I wondered, why should I be so<br>
upset when someone else has found the truth, as we have?  If more people <br>
live healthily, who should we be to complain? <br>
<p>
Seventh-day Adventism is not by nature an original religion in any case.<br>
We're not upset because the Jews or the Seventh-day Baptists got to the <br>
Sabbath first.  Luther figured out about the priesthood of all believers<br>
and justification by faith long before we did.  The goal of all churches<br>
which claim uniqueness, and the Mormons and Catholics both join us in this<br>
claim, is that we reflect the New Testament church in doctrine and practice.<br>
Obviously this gives three orthogonal views of what the church must have <br>
been like.  <br>
<p>
If you have felt threatened by either of the two articles on Mormon<br>
health messages, try to examine why, and please post why.  Of course,<br>
we must also recognize that quite a similar health message has been in <br>
Islam for hundreds of years, although it may or may not have been<br>
known to E.G. White and J. Smith.  Does anyone want to put forth the case<br>
that one should choose Islam on these grounds?<br>
<p>
Steve Timm<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
