On Sun, 1 Mar 1992 10:10:40 -0500 (EST) you said:<br>
<i>&gt;Some SDAs point to the health principles advocated by Ellen White as</i><br>
<i>&gt;being unique and far ahead of the thinking of her time.  I would like</i><br>
<i>&gt;to share some passages with you that were written by a nonSDA</i><br>
<i>&gt;religious leader between 1851 and 1877.  (EGW's first health vision</i><br>
<i>&gt;dates to 1860s)  He talks of the dangers of tobacco, alcohol, coffee,</i><br>
<i>&gt;and tea, advocates a vegetarian diet and simplicity in diet, sleeping</i><br>
<i>&gt;and living in fresh, pure air.</i><br>
<p>
  And BY was following the lead of Joseph Smith Jr, who in 1833 gave us<br>
what is now Section 89 (the Word of Wisdom) of the Doctrine and Covenants.<br>
  In it eating meat is suppose to be in moderation (actual words are<br>
'times of famine or excess hunger') and grains are to be used more.  In<br>
it is also the promise to all that follow these words of wisdom that<br>
they will have health, wisdom, knowledge and strength.<br>
