	In my opinion, yes.  I think my thought is well put in Ministry<br>
of Healing, page 98 (my version).  "The theory of mind control was<br>
originated by Satan, to introduce himself as the chief worker, to put<br>
human philosophy where divine philosophy should be.  Of all the errors<br>
that are finding acceptance among professedly Christian people, none is<br>
a more dangerous deception, none more certain to separate man from God,<br>
than this."<br>
	The way I see it, if it isn't the Holy Spirit leading people to<br>
babtism, who is?  Then I would have to ask, what has any significance,<br>
babtism with water or babtism of the Holy Spirit?<br>
	I hope this isn't SOP bashing.  (I think Paul would give the<br>
same answer am.)  But it's my honest opinion that this could be the ground<br>
work which with liberty of conscience is taken away.  For if it's ok to<br>
manipulate people... isn't it ok to force people if it's supposedly for<br>
their own good?<br>
<p>
	As with all my opinions, this is subject to change as I become<br>
slightly less ignorant.<br>
