Steve Timm: Perhaps you could send this to Dave by EMAIL. I will leave<br>
that to your discretion!! &lt;&lt;Paul&gt;&gt;<br>
<p>
Dan I agree with you. I know and have had experience with evangelists<br>
that have done this (manipulating) and we only live to see the evil<br>
effects of this kind of action. I cannot understand when some try to take<br>
things into their "hands." -- Why they do not allow the Holy Spirit to do<br>
its works.<br>
<p>
When I was living in Lansing, MI I had the privilege of baptizing a couple<br>
who were our neighbors. When it came down to the place for them to make a<br>
decision about being baptized and joining the church -- after I had<br>
discussed it with them, I said to them, "Why don't you pray about this and<br>
give it some more thought and you can let me know your decision later this<br>
week." This was Sunday morning and Wednesday noon the husband called me<br>
and said, "We have decided we want to be baptized and join the church." I<br>
felt that I gave the Holy Spirit an opportunity to work on their hearts.<br>
They are faithful members today after 10 years and have visited us twice<br>
since we have been in Maryland.<br>
<p>
Sad to say though this is not how is usually works with our evangelists.<br>
They put undue pressure on people for a decision and then later the people<br>
regret what they have done.<br>
<p>
&lt;&lt;Paul&gt;&gt;<br>
