The president of our conference lead out in an evangelistic series.<br>
A couple of the church elders at the sponsoring church approached him<br>
asking that at the alter call, that they go forward to help "prime the<br>
pump".  They were encouraged to do so.  I suspect that this is not all<br>
that uncommon.  In our church we have a retired pastoral couple.  Every<br>
single time there is an alter call -- regular church service, or<br>
evangelistic series, even calls for baptismal volunteers -- they are<br>
the first to rush forward.  I doubt they ask anyone for 'permission',<br>
they just do it.  That is a bit different from having the evangelist<br>
encourage people to help 'prime the pump'.<br>
<p>
Dave<br>
