<title>Mar_1992: Re: What is Lab 1</title>
<h1>Re: What is Lab 1</h1>
Dave Buxton (<i>davidbu@loowit.wr.tek.com</i>)<br>
<i>Thu, 05 Mar 92 08:51:07 PST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#31">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#31">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#31">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#31">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0032.html">Nancy Vyhmeister: "Re: Iniquities, Transgressions, Sins, etc."</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0030.html">Patricio Navia: "Iniquities, Transgressions, Sins, etc."</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
The question was asked, several SDAnet posts ago, what is Lab 1.<br>
<p>
The 'inventers' of NLP have developed a series of seminars/classes<br>
that span several labs.  What is taught depends a whole lot upon<br>
the instructor.   Many Lab 1 instructors have felt very uncomfortable<br>
about the NLP material they were taught and so what they teach in<br>
Lab 1 is considerably watered down from what the class might be if<br>
taught by the authors of the program, or more enthusiastic advocates<br>
of the material.  An typical SDA Lab 1 would be a lot different from a <br>
xxxxx church Lab 1.  So, Lab 1 can range all overn the map, depending<br>
on the instructor and his/her scruples.  Lab 2, ect, are much more likely<br>
to get into real NLP material.  Hence the frequent protests that<br>
hey, "I took Lab 1 and there was nothing wrong with it".  Tell me,<br>
would you drink water that came from an arsenic tainted spring, or<br>
industrial wastes contaminated well, if the guy selling the water<br>
insisted that the water had been run through a special filter to take<br>
out the poison?  And to prove it he drinks down a glass full.<br>
<p>
Psychologists say that nobody can be hypnotised if they don't want<br>
to be hypnotised.  That is what they used to say about old style<br>
classical hypnosis.  That is the supposed 'beauty' of NLP, that<br>
more people become vulnerable to manipulation because they don't<br>
know what is happening to them.  You are not nearly as vulnerable<br>
if you can recognize the techniques potentially being used on you.<br>
<p>
And, there are so many sources of pure water, why go to a sourse of<br>
poison water that has been supposedly purified and made fit for the<br>
church and its leadership and members?<br>
<p>
Dave (David E. Buxton)<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
