To Glen McCloskey<br>
<p>
Glen, I hate to hear horror stories about long altar calls etc. I may<br>
leave myself open for some criticism by some but anyway here goes.<br>
<p>
Usually I use a card for people to fill in and make their choice and then<br>
I visit with them either after the service or at their home. I really<br>
believe it is a sweet experience to have a person make their decision in<br>
their home -- may I say, in the privacy of their home. As I have said in<br>
other messages, I further believe that we should allow the person to make<br>
that decision on their own. We have a congregation in some cities of<br>
people who have been baptized under pressure and then never come back to<br>
church. Then the pastor has to deal with those people for years on end.<br>
<p>
&lt;&lt;Paul&gt;&gt;<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
