<i>&gt; I'm having doubts again.  Many of my friends are telling me that I am</i><br>
<i>&gt; acting like a modern Jonah. Could that be true? </i><br>
<p>
There are countries around the world that do not accept any "missionaries".<br>
The GC offers a placement service for those with technical qualificaitions<br>
willing to be part time as missionaries.  To illustrate -- you could work<br>
for IBM in some country open to IBM but not to missionaries, with the<br>
understanding from IBM that you get to take time off from time to time<br>
to hold an evangelistic series or  . . . . . . . .<br>
I forget the name of the placement service, but you could contact AVSC<br>
(Adventist Volunteer Service Corp)  perhaps they are the ones.  AVSC<br>
seems to be more for retired folks willing to help out around the world<br>
where room and board are provided but not transportation and other<br>
expenses.<br>
<p>
Dave<br>
