<!-- body="start" -->
Dr. Loveless is the senior pastor at Loma Linda.  He has also been<br>
offering pastoral seminars in new meditative forms of prayer.  Those<br>
who are familiar with eastern meditative styes have objected.  One<br>
person, doing a study of the Jesuits and their founder Ignatious<br>
Loyola, found a remarkable parallel between the script that Loveless<br>
was following with his ministerial seminars and what Loyola put his<br>
Jesuits through.  Then more recently Dr. Loveless started offering<br>
hand outs of his methodology of prayer and meditation.  About half<br>
way down his included Bibliography is Loyola's book in which is documented<br>
much the same material.   I have relatives at Loma Linda who say he<br>
prefers not to use the pulpit, prefering at times to simply sit on<br>
the floor during his sermons.<br>
 <br>
Does anyone out there know anything about Dr. Loveless?<br>
 <br>
Dave<br>
 <br>
[Please, some of the silent majority from LLU, LSU, or CUC (where he<br>
was before, speak up!  I am also echoing this post to SDA-L because they<br>
have a lot more coverage in California, so some of you will get it twice.<br>
We want the facts.  SCT]<br>
