Dave, From my observations of the SDA church I do not sense the<br>
denomination trying to control what people believe. I believe there is<br>
more "freedom" of thought in the church then there has previously been. I<br>
think we owe this freedom to individuals like Bob Brimsmead and Des Ford.<br>
This has caused many SDAs,to re study our position on the teachings of<br>
the Bible and know for certainty why we believe what we do.<br>
<p>
There are and have been individuals that appear to be conservative<br>
legalists  -- it is these people who are trying to pour us into "their<br>
mold" of Adventist theology. And believe there is no room for discussion<br>
unity in diversity.<br>
<p>
&lt;&lt;Paul&gt;&gt;<br>
