<title>Mar_1992: Creationist mailing list net</title>
<h1>Creationist mailing list net</h1>
callen roy (<i>allenroy@rigel.cs.pdx.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Fri, 13 Mar 92 21:19:11 PST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#61">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#61">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#61">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#61">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0062.html">Steven Timm: "Re: SDA subculture"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0060.html">Steven Timm: "Re: Defining Catholic vs Protestant"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
The following is from a fellow christian whom I met on talk.origins.<br>
He is starting up an e-mail net list to christains who wish to<br>
discuss origins from a christain point of view, to offer thoughts<br>
and assistance for those who are posting on talk.origins or just<br>
talking with each other.  If you want on his list mail to his<br>
address at the end of his note.  C. Allen Roy<br>
---------------------------------------------------------------<br>
<p>
Hello fellow Creationists,<br>
<p>
I think a Christian Creationist mailing list is a good idea but<br>
I'm unsure how to go about setting one up or what to say. The<br>
tone most evolutionists use, along with the name calling get on<br>
my nerves after awhile, and there are so many evolutionists that<br>
I find it difficult to pray for them all. <br>
<p>
Recently, I exchanged some email with Matt Brinkman who is an<br>
evolutionist and Christian (I guess that gets interpreted as: <br>
theistic evolutionist). We were't communicating too well and <br>
ended up arguing back and forth over who was being sincere, and<br>
both of us were using the principles taught in Matthew 18:15-17 <br>
which discusses what to do when a brother sins against you.<br>
We've discussed the situation and have decided to start it up<br>
again next week after we've rested on the weekend. We'll be<br>
communicating via email, not posting in talk.origins.<br>
<p>
One of my main concerns in talk.origins is our relationships<br>
with fellow believers who are also evolutionists. Another concern<br>
is how we repond to the non-believers who are also evolutionists.<br>
I'm sure we all realize the importance of our postings being read <br>
by many people, mostly lurkers just reading once, twice or more.<br>
The impression we leave on these individuals is very important. <br>
I don't think I'm telling you something you haven't already heard<br>
or know, I just sometimes need a reminder that the non-believer<br>
is watching the Christian as if they were under a microscope.<br>
<p>
I'd like to get to know all of you, so please don't be shy. I'd<br>
like to tell you where I'm coming from and why I post to talk.origins,<br>
but that'll have to wait for a future date. <br>
<p>
I'd like to encourage you to continue to fight the good fight and<br>
to pray for those in talk.origins, that are what I believe to be<br>
misguided as far as origins are concerned. <br>
<p>
I don't know where this mailing list will lead and I can make no<br>
promises, I even have doubts as to even starting it up, but Lord<br>
willing, we'll continue and hopefully encourage each other in <br>
the process.<br>
<p>
Take care,<br>
<p>
Jim Loucks           jloucks@uts.amdahl.com <br>
{apple, pyramid, sun, uunet}!amdahl!jloucks<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
