Helli all,<br>
<p>
<i>&gt;	One other interesting note.  This book said that Seventh-day Adventists</i><br>
<i>&gt;	are "Fundamentalist Pentecostal Protestants."  Although SDAs deny that</i><br>
<i>&gt;	they are "pentecostal", the real world thinks SDAs ARE!  I wonder what</i><br>
<i>&gt;	this is based on.  I would venture that as more "Celebration Churches"</i><br>
<i>&gt;	form, this opinion will get stronger among outsiders.</i><br>
<p>
I once read a publication from an ex-Jesuit that explained the way that<br>
the Vatican considered the various protestant denominations for the purpose<br>
of furthering ecumentism. This plan was to first make stronger ties between<br>
small groups of religions which they put together according to their <br>
views of which religions would be easier to merge together. Interestingly<br>
the SDAs the pentecostals and some other religions were clustered together.<br>
<p>
<p>
Ruben. <br>
