<!-- body="start" -->
To SDAnet,<br>
<p>
The following excerpts of the countries with SDA listed is taken from<br>
"THE WORLD FACTBOOK 1990 ELECTRONIC VERSION."  It's interesting how<br>
the CIA usually considers SDA as a Christian organization, but not<br>
Protestant -- hence, lumping SDA with Jehovah's Witnesses and Latter<br>
Day Saints.  (See Kiribati, Federated States of Micronesia, and<br>
Netherlands Antilles in comparison with Belize.)  Note that the<br>
countries are all non-major ones (well, except maybe Netherlands<br>
Antilles -- Schlumberger (pronounced "Sh-lum-bur-jay") Limited, for<br>
tax purposes, is headquartered there :-).<br>
<p>
Danny (a Schlumberger employee)<br>
---------------------<br>
<p>
Country:  Belize<br>
Religion: 60% Roman Catholic; 40% Protestant (Anglican, Seventh-Day<br>
Adventist, Methodist, Baptist, Jehovah's Witnesses, Mennonite)<br>
<p>
Country:  Bermuda<br>
(dependent territory of the UK)<br>
Religion: 37% Anglican, 14% Roman Catholic, 10% African Methodist<br>
Episcopal (Zion), 6% Methodist, 5% Seventh-Day Adventist, 28% other<br>
<p>
Country:  British Virgin Islands<br>
(dependent territory of the UK)<br>
Religion: majority Methodist; others include Anglican, Church of God,<br>
Seventh-Day Adventist, Baptist, and Roman Catholic<br>
<p>
Country:  Falkland Islands (Islas Malvinas)<br>
(dependent territory of the UK)<br>
Religion: primarily Anglican, Roman Catholic, and United Free Church;<br>
Evangelist Church, Jehovah's Witnesses, Lutheran, Seventh-Day Adventist<br>
<p>
Country:  Kiribati<br>
Religion: 48% Roman Catholic, 45% Protestant (Congregational),<br>
some Seventh-Day Adventist and Baha'i<br>
<p>
Country:  Micronesia, Federated States of<br>
Religion: predominantly Christian, divided between Roman Catholic and<br>
Protestant; other churches include Assembly of God, Jehovah's Witnesses,<br>
Seventh-Day Adventist, Latter Day Saints, and the Baha'i Faith<br>
<p>
Country:  Montserrat<br>
(dependent territory of the UK)<br>
Religion: Anglican, Methodist, Roman Catholic, Pentecostal, Seventh-Day<br>
Adventist, other Christian denominations<br>
<p>
Country:  Netherlands Antilles<br>
(part of the Dutch realm)<br>
Religion: predominantly Roman Catholic; Protestant, Jewish,<br>
Seventh-Day Adventist<br>
<p>
Country:  Niue<br>
(free association with New Zealand)<br>
Religion: 75% Ekalesia Nieue (Niuean Church)--a Protestant<br>
church closely related to the London Missionary Society, 10% Mormon, 5% Roman<br>
Catholic, Jehovah's Witnesses, Seventh-Day Adventist<br>
<p>
Country:  Norfolk Island<br>
(territory of Australia)<br>
Religion: Anglican, Roman Catholic, Uniting Church in<br>
Australia, and Seventh-Day Adventist<br>
<p>
Country:  Pitcairn Islands<br>
(dependent territory of the UK)<br>
Religion: 100% Seventh-Day Adventist<br>
 <br>
Country:  St. Helena<br>
(dependent territory of the UK)<br>
Religion: Anglican majority; also Baptist, Seventh-Day Adventist,<br>
and Roman Catholic<br>
<p>
Country:  St. Vincent and the Grenadines<br>
Religion: Anglican, Methodist, Roman Catholic, Seventh-Day Adventist<br>
<p>
Country:  Sao Tome and Principe<br>
Religion: Roman Catholic, Evangelical Protestant, Seventh-Day Adventist<br>
<p>
Country:  Solomon Islands<br>
Religion: almost all at least nominally Christian; Anglican, Seventh-Day<br>
Adventist, and Roman Catholic Churches dominant<br>
<p>
Country:  Turks and Caicos Islands<br>
(dependent territory of the UK)<br>
Religion: Anglican, Roman Catholic, Baptist, Methodist, Church of God,<br>
Seventh-Day Adventist<br>
<p>
Country:  Western Samoa<br>
Religion: 99.7% Christian (about half of population associated with the<br>
London Missionary Society; includes Congregational, Roman Catholic, Methodist,<br>
Latter Day Saints, Seventh-Day Adventist)<br>
<p>
---------------------<br>
Just for comparisons:<br>
<p>
Country:  United States<br>
Religion: Protestant 61% (Baptist 21%, Methodist 12%, Lutheran 8%,<br>
Presbyterian 4%, Episcopalian 3%, other Protestant 13%), Roman Catholic 25%,<br>
Jewish 2%, other 5%; none 7%<br>
[I wonder where SDA is placed in this statistics.]<br>
<p>
Country:  Japan<br>
Religion: most Japanese observe both Shinto and Buddhist rites; about 16%<br>
belong to other faiths, including 0.8% Christian<br>
<p>
---------------------<br>
