<title>Mar_1992: Time magazine February 24, 1992</title>
<h1>Time magazine February 24, 1992</h1>
Steven Timm (<i>st0o+@andrew.cmu.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Fri, 27 Mar 1992 23:48:22 -0500 (EST)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#81">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#81">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#81">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#81">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0082.html">Steven Timm: "1992 Youth Evangelism International Workshop"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0080.html">McCluskey G: "life and death"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
The cover story of Time magazine on February 24, 1992 was HOLY ALLIANCE,<br>
detailing for the first time the extensive cooperation between the<br>
Reagan administration and the Vatican in the support of Solidarity in<br>
Poland.<br>
During the seven years that Solidarity was underground, 1981-1988,<br>
the church was the primary conduit to the Solidarity leaders of news from <br>
the West, as well as a means of channeling funds, fax machines, and much else.<br>
<p>
Diplomatic recognition of the Vatican and the US shift away from funding<br>
birth control family planning programs in third world countries were<br>
both direct results of this alliance.  <br>
<p>
The article makes for fascinating reading.<br>
<p>
Steve Timm<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
