<title>Mar_1992: Books on race relations</title>
<h1>Books on race relations</h1>
Steven Timm (<i>st0o+@andrew.cmu.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Wed,  1 Apr 1992 11:48:12 -0500 (EST)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#85">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#85">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#85">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#85">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0084.html">Nancy Vyhmeister: "Re: South Africa Votes"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
A recent book that came out on the topic of race relations in the church <br>
is Righteous Rebel, being a biography of W. W. Fordham.<br>
<p>
His career began at Oakwood College where he was one of the leaders of <br>
the 1932 student strike which demanded a Black president for that<br>
institution.  It chronicles the advances that have been made over the<br>
years in race relations.<br>
<p>
If you are looking for a research work, I would suggest Seeking A Sanctuary<br>
by Bull and Lockhart.  There is an extensive section in this book on <br>
race relations in the SDA church.<br>
<p>
<p>
Steve Timm<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
