<title>Dec_1992: "Independent ministries"</title>
<h1>"Independent ministries"</h1>
Ruben Gonzalez (<i>ruben@ee.uts.edu.au</i>)<br>
<i>Fri, 4 Dec 92 14:40:57 EST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#30">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#30">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#30">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#30">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0031.html">Steven Timm: "Unexpected album reviews"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0029.html">Steven Timm: "Two lessons both sides should learn in independent ministries"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
<li> <b>Next in thread:</b> <a href="0033.html">cheryl berthelsen: "Re:  "Independent ministries""</a>
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
Hi all,<br>
<p>
	Tony writes :<br>
<p>
<i>&gt;In Australia we don't have the diversity of independent ministries</i><br>
<i>&gt;that exist in the US, but we certainly have our per capita fair share.</i><br>
<i>&gt;They accuse the organisation of ignoring divine counsel or whatever,&gt;</i><br>
<i>&gt;the organisation tries its hardest to ignore them, the conferences</i><br>
<i>&gt;complain about tithe being diverted, and the situation continues to</i><br>
<i>&gt;worsen.</i><br>
<p>
<i>&gt;I'm tired of seeing the church (and others) attacked by publications</i><br>
<i>&gt;such as "The Remnant Herald", "The Protestant", those anti-celebration</i><br>
<i>&gt;videos, and a whole lot of other items I have been fortunate enough</i><br>
<i>&gt;to avoid. It is also disturbing to see the church authorities responding</i><br>
<i>&gt;in kind (well, almost).</i><br>
<p>
I'd just like to qualify this by saying that the independant ministries<br>
in Australia are not in the same league as those in the US. Most of the <br>
independent ministries I know of are very small, typically just one lay<br>
member running his own printing press. Most of these are not anti-SDA church<br>
and you won't see them denouncing the church. <br>
<p>
I am not aware of "The Remnant Herald" but I am aware of the "The Protestant".<br>
This latter one should I say is comprised of a fair proportion of non-SDA's<br>
who like to spend their time accusing the church of being Babylon.<br>
<p>
Being aware of the independant minstries in the US like Weimar college and<br>
Hartlands and Pr. Ron Spear's group etc which are by and large very supportive<br>
of the church (Even though they might not agree with everything that goes on).<br>
I can say that groups like the ones that publish "The Protestant" would have<br>
absolutely nothing in common.<br>
<p>
Ruben.<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
