<title>Dec_1992: Two lessons both sides should learn in independent ministries</title>
<h1>Two lessons both sides should learn in independent ministries</h1>
Steven Timm (<i>st0o+@andrew.cmu.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Thu,  3 Dec 1992 22:13:21 -0500 (EST)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#29">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#29">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#29">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#29">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0030.html">Ruben Gonzalez: ""Independent ministries""</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0028.html">Richard Mazzaferri: "The Catholic face of Adventism?  (Was Re: NAD action on private organizations)"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
1)  Inspired writings are for educating oneself, not clubbing others.<br>
<p>
2)  Ordination conveys neither infallibility  nor corruption.<br>
<p>
Steve Timm<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
