<!-- body="start" -->
It sems that the E.G. White Estates is going to drag their feet about<br>
allowing unix systems to access their CD rom.  They are still not sure<br>
that they are willing to allow multiple access to the CD rom or not.<br>
They don't know about multi-user systems, networks, or the internet and<br>
don't want to jeperdize the sale of the CD's for PC's.  All of the<br>
original books are no longer covered under the copyright laws, but there<br>
is still some question about whether the same material can be<br>
copyrighted when put onto a newer form of media such as the CD.<br>
<p>
They don't want to "release" anything until they have corrected some<br>
of the typo's in the current data.  This should be done by next summer.<br>
<pre>
-- 
Daniel R. Bidwell	|	bidwell@andrews.edu
Andrews University	Computer Science &amp; Information Systems Department
If two always agree, one of them is unnecesary
"Friends don't let friends do DOS"
</pre>
