I read Cheryl's article with interest.  I was also upset by that<br>
Review article, for a slightly different reason.  I found that it<br>
misrepresented the character and actions of at least a couple of the<br>
independent ministries.  Also, it made no mention of the departure<br>
from divine counsel that has led to the formation of so many<br>
independent ministries.  A friend of mine who doesn't even like those<br>
ministries thought that that article was self-righteous.<br>
<p>
I think the church leadership panicked when there was a non-approved<br>
ordination at Steps to Life recently.  They feared that a new church<br>
was forming and acted a little irrationally.  I hope that things will<br>
calm down now and that they will correct some of the errors in that<br>
article.<br>
<p>
	Dave Plaisted<br>
