<i>&gt; All ,</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; Hie everybody . This is Colin Chibafa and basically I'd just like to say</i><br>
<i>&gt; I've enjoyed being on the SDAnet , but unfortunately our University</i><br>
<i>&gt; closes next week (officially on the 12th of December , but I am leaving</i><br>
<i>&gt; on the 10th after my last exam) , and after that I don't think I will</i><br>
<i>&gt; have much access to the internet as I will be returning home to Bulawayo</i><br>
<i>&gt; ... a good 430 odd kilometres from here !</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; I have found the discussions interesting , although at times I've really</i><br>
<i>&gt; wondered what has become of us as Christians ... I'm refering to the</i><br>
<i>&gt; incidents regarding the mentally-ill and the last one regarding Joe and</i><br>
<i>&gt; his bathroom problems . I personally think throwing some-one from church</i><br>
<i>&gt; (of all places) , because they have some disagreeable personal traits</i><br>
<i>&gt; smacks of intollerance . Anyway , are we saying we are somehow of more</i><br>
<i>&gt; value before God than that poor individual  . I am sure we do not</i><br>
<i>&gt; understand the devastation this has on the poor guy . I feel so strongly</i><br>
<i>&gt; about this , because I have heard of the impact this can have on an</i><br>
<i>&gt; individual . Let me expound on that . This one guy happened to be</i><br>
<i>&gt; visiting South-Africa and on Sabbath decided to go to church .</i><br>
<i>&gt; Unfortunately , he went to to the "wrong" neighbourhood and to his</i><br>
<i>&gt; disbelief , a pastor whom he knew , but didn't really know him came to</i><br>
<i>&gt; him with the sad news that he was in the wrong church and offered him</i><br>
<i>&gt; the directions to the church where he would be more at home . this</i><br>
<i>&gt; pastor had once worked in Zimbabwe .</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; This affected individual was really stunned . Talk of worshipping the</i><br>
<i>&gt; same God .</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; Anyways , it always seems in such situations , how the Joes of this</i><br>
<i>&gt; world are affected is of no consequence as long as we are surrounded by</i><br>
<i>&gt; those we can tolerate ... no problem . I think a greater degree of</i><br>
<i>&gt; tolerance on our part is essential ... the church is not a social club</i><br>
<i>&gt; where only those of a certain class can be accepted as members !</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; Besides that , it was well hearing from you all . God bless and I know</i><br>
<i>&gt; most likely we will never meet this side of heaven , but Lord willing i</i><br>
<i>&gt; hope to meet you all by the sea of Glass .</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; "Whatsoever things are true ... think upon such things !" - Phil. 4:8</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; Colin</i><br>
