<!-- body="start" -->
Paul Gates' mention of The Lamp and Word Search reminded me of my search<br>
for PC Bible search software a year or so ago.  There are all kinds of<br>
packages at all kinds of prices.  However, the package that I use is<br>
zero-cost shareware, i.e., "freeware":  OnLine Bible.<br>
<p>
OLB was originally developed by Larry Price in Ontario, Canada (a friend<br>
of mine met Larry; evidently he's a neat Christian and a real scholar); however,<br>
there are now numerous contributors (sorta like GNU and the Free Software<br>
Foundation), one of whom -- Mark Fuller -- works for Motorola here in Phoenix.<br>
Mark has made OLB 6.0 available for anonymous FTP via wuarchive.wustl.com<br>
(IP address 128.252.135.4) under /doc/bible/ibm-pc.  If you don't have<br>
Internet access, I know that some Christian shareware publishers carry it.<br>
<p>
The README.TXT file from wuarchive follows: -----------------------------------<br>
<p>
                       OnLine Bible version 6.<br>
                              FreeWare<br>
                            Copy Freely<br>
-----------------------------------------------------------------------<br>
This document contains:<br>
 <br>
 1- A listing of all modules available, including:<br>
    - zip contents with dates (for determining if you need an update).<br>
    - the text for use on the disk label.<br>
    - approximate disk space used after installation.<br>
 <br>
 2- Instructions for installing OLB and email source for help.<br>
 <br>
 3- What is OLB?  (a brief intro to the program)<br>
-----------------------------------------------------------------------<br>
