-----------------------------------------------------------------------<br>
Installation:<br>
 <br>
  The basic setup consists of the following modules:<br>
    1 OLB program<br>
   11 AV-Darby text modules<br>
    2 Cross Reference modules<br>
    4 Lexicon modules<br>
    4 Topic modules<br>
 <br>
  Installation must be done from floppy.  Before any installing can be<br>
  done, you must un'zip the modules to floppy disks.   All zip's are<br>
  designed to be unzipped from a hard disk onto one 360k floppy each. If<br>
  you are using a higher density disk you may place as many module<br>
  pieces on it as will fit on a disk.  For instance, if you are using<br>
  1.44 floppies.  You can put all the AV-DBY text modules on 3 disks,<br>
  laying them out in numerical order per disk.  Be sure to label the<br>
  disks so you can insert the correct disk when prompted.<br>
 <br>
  [Note: If you need pkunzip, it can be found at /mirrors/msdos/zip<br>
  filename is pkz110eu.exe.  This is a self extracting zip -- by<br>
  executing the program it will produce the pkunzip program.]<br>
 <br>
 <br>
First Time Install:<br>
 <br>
  Place the OLB program disk (the one you un'zipped OLBnnnn.ZIP onto) in<br>
  your drive and type: GO.  This will display some info and prompt you<br>
  to type INSTALL.<br>
 <br>
  Once the program portion of OLB is installed, an additional install<br>
  menu will appear.  By selecting 'a' on that menu, you may install<br>
  Texts, Cross Refs, Notes, Lexicons, etc.<br>
 <br>
 <br>
Installing More Modules at a Later Date:<br>
 <br>
  Place your OLB program disk in the drive and type INSTALL.  The<br>
  Install program will sense you already have the programs installed and<br>
  will ask you if you want to re-install them.  Answer 'NO', and proceed<br>
  to the install screen where you can install more modules.<br>
 <br>
 <br>
Assistance:<br>
 <br>
  If you are having problems with the install, try booting from a floppy<br>
  before running 'install'.<br>
 <br>
  If you are trying to run install from the hard disk, please go back a<br>
  few paragraphs and re-read the install instructions.  OLB is not<br>
  designed to install from the hard disk -- it must be done from floppy.<br>
 <br>
  A common problem reported is a 'crc' error due to unzipping on<br>
  a non-MS-DOS platform.  If you get a 'crc' error during install:<br>
  be sure you pkunziped in a real MS-DOS environment.<br>
 <br>
  If you need help, you may send e-mail to<br>
    acus10@waccvm.corp.mot.com<br>
 <br>
  Please provide some detail about the problem, your equipment, any<br>
  special software your running, etc.  And please provide your e-mail<br>
  address in your note.<br>
 <br>
------------------------------------------------------------<br>
OLB overview<br>
-----------<br>
The Online Bible<br>
 <br>
_What is New in Version 6 from Version 5?_<br>
 <br>
o Huge topic disk includes over 4200 topics from the original<br>
Thompson Chain plus hundreds of topics from the 1897 New<br>
Topical Textbook plus much other resource material.<br>
o Strong's numbers carefully revised, find an error and win $10<br>
o 100,000 verb parsings added to Authorised Version<br>
o English frequency counts added to Hebrew Lexicon<br>
o Greek lexicon heavily revised for accuracy<br>
o 580,474 cross references for the whole Bible<br>
o Bilingual Versions, AV plus Strong's plus European languages<br>
o Hypertext features added to Notes facility, point and shoot<br>
o Up to four independent sets of notes can be accessed in a carousel<br>
o Alternate lexicon for your word studies<br>
o Updated 1833 Webster Bible included free with AV versions<br>
o Manual completely rewritten by a professional English publisher<br>
 <br>
_Scholar's Pack Description_<br>
o Requires about 14 megabytes on a hard disk on IBM PC, 384K<br>
and DOS 2.11 or later.<br>
o The basic text for the Online Bible is the 1769 Authorised Version<br>
(AV or KJV) indexed using Strong's numbers. The 1833 Webster<br>
update is included free as a footnote toggle. Also the extremely<br>
accurate 1890 Darby version is part of the base package. Other<br>
Bible texts are available.<br>
o 100,000 verbs parsings and definitions<br>
o English definitions of Biblical Greek and Hebrew words.<br>
Knowledge of Greek and Hebrew is NOT required.<br>
o Lexicon based on Thayer's and Smith's Bible Dictionary plus<br>
others; this is keyed to the large Kittel and the Theological<br>
Dictionary of the New Testament. The Old Testament is Brown,<br>
Driver, Briggs, Gesenius Lexicon; this is keyed to the<br>
"Theological Word Book of the Old Testament."<br>
o Lexicon is in text format and you can easily change it using UED.<br>
o 580,474 cross references from the Treasury of Scripture<br>
Knowledge and others. You can instantly recall and display the<br>
cross references.<br>
o Menu driven design with extensive context sensitive helps<br>
o Almost any monitor can be used. Supports 43-line EGA, 28-line<br>
VGA, and 50-line VGA, and others.<br>
o Complete search facilities include, word, phrase, multiple words,<br>
and much more. Searches may use AND, OR and NOT operators<br>
to select verses. Searches may be restricted.<br>
o You can search using Strong's numbers and access the definitions.<br>
You can print a passage with all the numbers and the definitions<br>
of the words used in that passage. This saves hours of time for<br>
those doing detailed Bible studies.<br>
o Verses can be selected for printing or saving to ASCII files for<br>
inclusion in most word processing documents.<br>
o TSR to copy verses directly into your word processors.<br>
o Quick Print for rapid printing of verses, notes, topics or<br>
definitions. Data can be accumulated to a file instead of being<br>
printed.<br>
o Printing can be attractively formatted with page breaks<br>
o Bulletin board version for users that would like to try the program<br>
or do not have a hard disk to run the program.<br>
o Visually Impaired option for use with screen reader hardware.<br>
o All verses displayed in context or out of context<br>
o You can add notes of any size to a verse using the supplied text<br>
processor.<br>
o Cross references can be added to notes for automatic recall.<br>
o You can define 32,767 topical entries.<br>
o Includes Topics Disk described in "Add-On Modules"<br>
o Dictionary of the words unique to the Bible allows you to spell<br>
check most documents having Bible passages.<br>
o NO ROYALTIES, DISTRIBUTE FREELY.<br>
o a combined AV and 1947 RSV is available also<br>
 <br>
Classical Package<br>
o Four Greek texts in one combined version, 1550 Stephanus,<br>
Scrivener 1894, Majority, and Nestle's<br>
o 1977 Stuttgartensia Hebrew Consonantal Text<br>
o Displays transliterated text on CGA and old monochrome monitors<br>
o Displays actual Greek and Hebrew on EGA and VGA monitors<br>
o Support included to print in Greek and Hebrew on most printers<br>
o This is not an interlinear, order only if you have had one year of<br>
Greek or Hebrew at a college.<br>
 <br>
Foreign Versions<br>
All bilingual versions include the AV and a foreign language text,<br>
Strong's numbers, verb parsings and the lexicons. The following<br>
foreign versions are available:<br>
 <br>
o Bilingual AV and Spanish 1989 RVA<br>
o Bilingual AV and French 1910 Louis Segond<br>
o Bilingual AV and German 190S or 1985 Darby Elberfelder<br>
o Bilingual AV and Dutch Saten Vertaling<br>
o Bilingual AV and Creole Version (Haiti)<br>
 <br>
Please write our European distributor for ordering and pricing<br>
information.<br>
 <br>
Peter van der Schelde,<br>
Online Bible Ministries, St. Publishare,<br>
P.O. Box 9187, 3301 AD Dordrecht, Netherlands,<br>
Tel: (31)- (0)78- 163853<br>
or Fax: (31) - (0)78 - 211111<br>
 <br>
New European languages are being added every month or so.<br>
Italian, Danish, Portuguese are planned for the next year.<br>
 <br>
Additional Add-On Modules<br>
We are creating add-on notes and topics modules for the Online<br>
Bible.<br>
 <br>
o Scofield Reference Bible Notes<br>
- the entire set of Scofield notes from the original Scofield<br>
Reference Bible<br>
- these are written exactly as in the original without any<br>
intentional changes<br>
 <br>
o Topics Disk<br>
- Original Thompson Chain References (Improved)<br>
- Westminster Confession of Faith<br>
- Spurgeon's Catechism<br>
- Torrey's New Topical Textbook<br>
- Bible and Science Questions and Answers<br>
- plus much other material<br>
- this module included free with all versions<br>
 <br>
o Treasury of Scripture Knowledge Verse Notes<br>
- entire text of the Treasury available<br>
- almost 600,000 cross references<br>
- much valuable Bible commentary and background information<br>
- in new easy to use format just point at a line of cross<br>
references for part of a verse and look at those verses.<br>
- this requires seven megs of hard disk space. If you have the<br>
room we strongly recommend that you get a copy.<br>
 <br>
Work-in-Progress<br>
The Greek text is being parsed and keyed to Strong's numbers.<br>
This should be ready by the middle of next year. After that we plan<br>
to do the Hebrew.<br>
 <br>
<pre>
