<!-- body="start" -->
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; First, I was amazed at the seemingly unchristian attitude portrayed in the</i><br>
<i>&gt; wording of the article.</i><br>
<p>
I was amazed and disappointed.<br>
<p>
<p>
<i>&gt;  Although it state specifically "this document is</i><br>
<i>&gt; not presented in a spirit of combat or hostility" is reeks of that spirit.</i><br>
<i>&gt; The words divisive or dissident appear in almost every paragraph.  There</i><br>
<i>&gt; are strong words such as "accuse", "rival", "competition". </i><br>
<p>
<p>
<p>
<i>&gt;      But the underlying motivition or thread in the article seemed to</i><br>
<i>&gt; be that these private "divisive" organizations were successfully</i><br>
<i>&gt; competing for tithe monies that the organized SDA church would like</i><br>
<i>&gt; coming to their coffers.  Sample statements of this idea: "They accuse</i><br>
<i>&gt; the SDA church of activities which may encourage members to divert</i><br>
<i>&gt; tithe to their private organizations rather than to the Church."</i><br>
<i>&gt; "According to the Bible plan the Church is supported by tithes and</i><br>
<i>&gt; offerings.</i><br>
<p>
Bingo.<br>
<p>
Another point was that these "divisive" groups actually had the<br>
audacity to schedule meetings during camp meeting times--a sure sign<br>
that they were trying to tear down Gods remnant church.<br>
<p>
The whole thing sounded rather petty to me.<br>
<p>
I am of the opinion that the SDA church is the only appropriate place to<br>
send your tithe, and that the groups mentioned (with the exception of<br>
Osborn's group) are clearly out of line.<br>
<p>
However, the method that the church is pursuing A) isn't going to<br>
win back any of the adherents to the divisive groups, and B) is irritating<br>
to loyal church members like myself, and C) just lends credibility to<br>
them by spending so much time berating them.<br>
<p>
I think the best strategy to pursue would be to simply lead by example:<br>
maintain the highest spiritual and fiscal standards in the leadership<br>
and operations of the church.  Instead of shutting down the divisive<br>
mills, just give them no grist.<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
