<title>Dec_1992: "Independent ministries"</title>
<h1>"Independent ministries"</h1>
Tony (<i>PHTH1@cc.newcastle.edu.au</i>)<br>
<i>04 Dec 1992 10:03:45 +1100</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#22">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#22">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#22">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#22">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0023.html">Gilbert Bailey: "NAD position on independent ministries"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0021.html">Tony: "Re: Church authority"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
I think it's about time this whole situation was brought into the<br>
open and faced up to by everybody - the administration, the ministry,<br>
and the grass-roots membership.<br>
<p>
In Australia we don't have the diversity of independent ministries<br>
that exist in the US, but we certainly have our per capita fair share.<br>
They accuse the organisation of ignoring divine counsel or whatever,<br>
the organisation tries its hardest to ignore them, the conferences<br>
complain about tithe being diverted, and the situation continues to<br>
worsen.<br>
<p>
I would like to see some open discussion at an *official* church<br>
function like a special conference session or camp meeting. Individuals<br>
like me should be given the chance to hear what the opposing sides<br>
(let's face it - they are!) have to say, and make up our minds where<br>
we stand. This would also give us a chance to have *our* say, so that<br>
the church leadership would end up with some idea where the average<br>
church member stands on these issues.<br>
<p>
I'm tired of seeing the church (and others) attacked by publications<br>
such as "The Remnant Herald", "The Protestant", those anti-celebration<br>
videos, and a whole lot of other items I have been fortunate enough<br>
to avoid. It is also disturbing to see the church authorities responding<br>
in kind (well, almost).<br>
<p>
Sometimes it seems that the church will not take a stand on these issues<br>
because it may mean losing more tithe etc.  For the record, I for one<br>
would be prepared to contribute more if it came to that. I would much<br>
rather see the church *admit* that some of the things that are said<br>
are true - if indeed they are - rather than try and fend off the attacks.<br>
<p>
If the independent groups feel uncomfortable with the church's position,<br>
then by all means let them form their own denomination, "Reformed<br>
Seventh-day Adventist Church" or whatever, and let us get on with more<br>
constructive things.<br>
<p>
Tony<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
