I like the comments which are being given, because they encourage me to<br>
believe that SDA young people aren't just reflecting other people's thoughts.<br>
The Church and it's institutions have helped you to be thinkers in your own<br>
right, even when you find yourself disagreeing in practice.<br>
<p>
I don't receive any church papers so don't know about the article first-hand.<br>
However, thanks to the Christian Behavioral Science/Social Work prof's. I was<br>
privilege to study under at Southern and Walla Walla College respectively,<br>
I dare believe to think that these "divisive" groups have sprung up because<br>
the church has failed to move in meeting the needs of the people.  Therefore,<br>
women who are denied equal recognition might not work to tare down the male<br>
establishment in the church, they simply put their money into their own work.<br>
<p>
Other "outcast" church groups do the same.  There is no need to panic, this is<br>
a part of God purifying His people.  However, let's pray that our <br>
church doesn't<br>
become a body where the brain tries to tell the fingernail, "I have no <br>
need of you."<br>
<p>
M<br>
----------<br>
