<!-- body="start" -->
I will first list some of the significant albums I didn't review.<br>
This would include Cindy Morgan, Michael Card, Angelo and Veronica,<br>
Sheila Walsh "Hymns and Voices"  and the collections from Wayne Watson,<br>
Twila Paris, and Margaret Becker, and Stephen Curtis Chapman's Great Adventure.<br>
<p>
Best new artist:  Maia Amada<br>
Best new group:  The Goads<br>
<p>
What follows is a list in rank order, followed in parenthesis<br>
by the rating I gave it.<br>
<p>
1.  Maia Amada  (4)<br>
2.  Susan Ashton "Angels of Mercy" (4)<br>
3.  Dick and Mel Tunney "Let The Dreamers Dream" (4)<br>
4.  Randy Stonehill "Wonderama"  (4)<br>
5.  First Call "Human Song" (3.5)<br>
6.  Lisa Bevill "Chaperone" (3.5)<br>
7.  Brett Barry "Adventure of a Lifetime" (3)<br>
8.  Tom Prasada-Rao "Incoming"  (3)<br>
9.  Michael W. Smith "Change Your World" (3)<br>
10.  The Goads  "Holy Territory"  (3)<br>
10.5  White Heart "Tales Of Wonder" (3)<br>
11.  Larnelle Harris "I Choose Joy" (3)<br>
12.  Ray Boltz "Seasons Change" (3)<br>
13.  Rich Mullins "The World....vol 2." (3)<br>
14.  Two Hearts "Stand Your Ground"  (2.5)<br>
15.  Crystal Lewis "Remember" (2.5)<br>
16.  Glad "Floodgates"  (2.5-3)<br>
17.  Tami Gunden "Behind The Cover"  (2.5)<br>
18.  Vince Ebo "Love is the better way"  (2)<br>
<p>
Mark Heard's album Satellite Sky is addressed in a separate article<br>
<p>
Special-purpose albums this year:<br>
(in no particular order)<br>
<p>
  Twila Paris "Sanctuary" (4)<br>
  Coram Deo (Peacock, O.O. Grey,Ashton, Card, English)  (3)<br>
  Amy Grant "Home For Christmas" (3)<br>
  Russ Taff "The Christmas Song" (3)<br>
  Handel's Messiah--a soulful celebration (4)<br>
<p>
As compared to previous Christmas albums<br>
 "The Promise"  Michael Card  (4)<br>
 "Michael W. Smith Christmas"  (4)<br>
 "Joy to the World"  Steve Green (2.5)<br>
<p>
Happy shopping, everyone!<br>
