<title>Dec_1992: The ten plus two commandments</title>
<h1>The ten plus two commandments</h1>
Steven Timm (<i>st0o+@andrew.cmu.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Sun,  6 Dec 1992 22:32:02 -0500 (EST)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#41">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#41">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#41">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#41">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0042.html">Steven Timm: "Re: What are Catholcis like today (Was NAD topic)"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0040.html">Steven Timm: "Re: The ten plus two commandments"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
<li> <b>Next in thread:</b> <a href="0040.html">Steven Timm: "Re: The ten plus two commandments"</a>
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
In the middle of a presentation on Biblical diet, I was struck by the<br>
fact that there are some other commandments other than the ten that are<br>
and have for a long time been part of SDA life, namely tithing and abstention<br>
from unclean meats.  <br>
<p>
I don't mean to question the validity of these two commands at all, but<br>
I wonder:  <br>
1)  Are there any other common duties incumbent on the SDA church member,<br>
in particular are any others sworn to in the baptismal vow?  I don't<br>
remember others.<br>
<p>
2)  Why don't we also make church members forswear such sins as pride and <br>
jealousy and contentiousness before baptism?<br>
<p>
As I think on #1 above the prohibitions against smoking and drinking<br>
come to mind.  But I would like to hear others, hopefully with Bible<br>
texts to back <br>
them up.<br>
<p>
Steve Timm<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
