<!-- body="start" -->
SDAnet,<br>
<p>
A correction to my previous post regarding independent ministries:<br>
<p>
The article I referred to in "Our Firm Foundation" by Ralph Larson did<br>
not say explicitly, "Send us your tithe."  What it did was ask rhetorically,<br>
"How can you financially support an organization which is in some degree<br>
of apostacy?" (Note a direct quote;  I am paraphrasing.)  While the author <br>
encourages the readers to support those pastors that are upholding the <br>
teachings of historic adventism, I have real problems with the way he sows <br>
distrust and division in the article; nonetheless, I should not have accused <br>
him of asking EXPLICITLY for tithe.<br>
<p>
Like others, I also am concerned that the Review article and insert may do <br>
more harm than good.<br>
<p>
Tim Swensen<br>
swensen@ecn.purdue.edu<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
