On vegetarianism, I myself am a vegetarian, but I don't see it as a sin<br>
to eat meat. Didn't Jesus eat meat? Weren't some of his disciples fishermen?<br>
All Jews had to eat the passover lamb, I don't think that there were many<br>
vegetarians then. Of course, it is good to be vegetarian, but to make such a<br>
big deal out of it is to major in minors.<br>
	Haven't we as a church got better things to do than spend time on<br>
arguing about minor details? (cf. Rom 14) <br>
	God bless,<br>
			Beng Tang.<br>
