Hi I'm first year science student.  I'm preparing for my final exam.  But<br>
one of my computer science happens to be this friday 6pm.  It's well over<br>
sunset and I don't want to write it since it's sabbath. <br>
I only have few days left and I don't know what to do?  I don't even know<br>
if the professor will be in his office.  And I need to know to whom I have<br>
to go to get a permission to postpone my exam till sabbath is over.<br>
	umpark@ccu.umanitoba.ca<br>
<p>
<p>
[First you should try to go to the professor.  If you can't find the<br>
professor, ask one of the secretaries in the department.  They should<br>
know<br>
if you can talk to the department head or if you need to go higher.<br>
You may also find that your negotiation position is improved if you <br>
ask to take the exam before instead of after, because this way they cannot <br>
acuse you of just not being ready.  Also there will be less worries about<br>
you talking to other people who have taken the test.<br>
<p>
Before you go to your professor, make sure you know your school's policy <br>
on religious discrimination.  SCT]<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
