The last time I remember baptisimal candidates going through the "27<br>
doctrines" was when I was baptized in 1967, and then it was only 13.  My<br>
observation here in Southeastern California (at least the Anglo churches)<br>
is that most baptisms are *not* accompanied by the candidate(s) publicly<br>
affirming these doctrines.... but then we are accused of strange and<br>
liberal ideas.<br>
I agree with those who find the simpler form more defensable, at least<br>
biblically.  Perhaps the SDA pioneers had it right in the 1860's, that the<br>
first step toward heresy is to "get up a creed."<br>
<p>
Dave J.<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
