I think there are better ways to spend our time than to discuss gum chewing<br>
in church.  For me its a personal matter, as long as it doesn't disrupt the<br>
church service for the others (blowing or popping bubbles, noisy chomping,<br>
or other annoying practices).  Let's get on with speading the gospel to the<br>
world.  I believe that as you get into a more and more meaningful experience<br>
with God, the answers for "minor" issues such as this become obvious.<br>
<p>
--Bruce<br>
