<title>Dec_1992: Independent Ministries</title>
<h1>Independent Ministries</h1>
Paul Gates (<i>70516.420@compuserve.com</i>)<br>
<i>09 Dec 92 17:38:50 EST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#71">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#71">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#71">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#71">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0072.html">Ruben Gonzalez: "Re: Chew Gum (Chiclets) in the Church..."</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0070.html">umpark@ccu.umanitoba.ca: "Please Upload this to everywhere."</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
Steve, and SDA Net.<br>
<p>
I could not resist adding a few of my own comments concerning the<br>
independent ministries. I read with interest the various comments as I<br>
paged through the SDA Net.<br>
<p>
We live within driving distance of Hartland Institute and my head elder in<br>
one of the churches that I pastor is the vice chairman on the board of<br>
Hartland. So, I feel that I know pretty much what is going on between<br>
Hartland and Hope International. Through the years some of the Independent<br>
Ministries have had a positive attitude towards things and people.<br>
<p>
I pastored the Laurel Brook Academy in Tennessee and consider the<br>
president, Robt. Zollinger a very good friend of mine. We also were in the<br>
army together for awhile till I shipped out for Korea and he went to<br>
Germany. They are good a good job educating our youth at Academy age.<br>
<p>
My wife and I were also acquainted with the Googe family at Little Creek<br>
Academy also in Tenn. near Knoxville. When I was pastoring in Tenn. Little<br>
Creek had a long waiting list of students that wanted to attend there.<br>
That was during the time when Little Creek was not accredited and Andrews<br>
University would not accept the credits of students going to Andrews from<br>
Little Creek. However, at that time the University of Tennessee in<br>
Knoxville was acquainted with the kind of education graduates of Little<br>
Creek were getting and made the blanket statement that they would accept<br>
any and all students from Little Creek Academy.<br>
<p>
I also have a high regard for Weimar Institute in Calif. They also are<br>
doing a good work. However, some of the other "rank and file" indep.<br>
Ministries is a different story.<br>
<p>
A little bit ago today I was talking to Marten Weber and David Newman at<br>
the General Conf. arranging speaking appts. for them in our churches in<br>
1993; David made this comment, "We have been doing church for 150 years,<br>
it is time that we found something that will change people and that is the<br>
cross!" That too, is my philosophy. This continual criticism of everything<br>
that is done by the denomination is really not accomplishing anything<br>
worth while in my opinion. <br>
<p>
I am sure that some of you at least have read Marten Weber's book on the<br>
"Tortured Conscience." In the book Marten gives some very current<br>
examples of what is going on in Hartland and other such institutions.<br>
<p>
When you have people who have nothing good to say about anything or<br>
anybody and are continuously saying that they are the remnant within the<br>
remnant -- it gets old after awhile. Ralph Larsen who writes in "Firm<br>
Foundation" is a retired minister and has nothing good to ever say about<br>
the denomination that I have ever read. Colin Standish is pretty much in<br>
the same camp. He has always had this "attitude" against the denomination<br>
even when he was teaching and later president of Columbia Union College.<br>
<p>
None of us are absolutely perfect and we will make mistakes but that is no<br>
cause to "scrap" the whole denomination. I receive the "Firm Foundation"<br>
every month and I have been looking for 5 years at least to find one good<br>
thing that the writers say about the denomination and have not found it<br>
yet. Maybe I missed it some place along the line!<br>
<p>
As some of you probably know the GC is publishing a document that will<br>
critique the teachings of Hope International, etc. I am not referring to<br>
the insert in the Adventist Review recently.<br>
<p>
..........Paul G.<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
