<title>Dec_1992: Thought on Indep. Ministries</title>
<h1>Thought on Indep. Ministries</h1>
Stan Macasieb (<i>macasib@rtsg.mot.com</i>)<br>
<i>Fri, 11 Dec 1992 13:09:55 -0600</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#81">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#81">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#81">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#81">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0082.html">umpark@ccu.umanitoba.ca: "Thanks for all"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0080.html">cheryl berthelsen : "Chewing gum may be important to the chewer"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
Hello,<br>
<p>
I know, it's been a while, but I think I have something.<br>
<p>
During our last church board meeting the pastor brought up the issue of<br>
indie ministries. He had a copy of "Issues", that paper cannon (or canon?)<br>
ball meant as a broadside to accusations made by certain ministries within<br>
the church. Most, if not all of the members present, seemed supportive of<br>
the GC in its response, a loving yet firm rebuttal. According to readers<br>
of the document, only about 1/3 of the document is actual verbage by the<br>
authors; the rest is footnotes and references to documents published by the<br>
ministries in question. <br>
<p>
Personally, I don't have the time right now to read it from cover-to-cover<br>
(I have a take-home final to take care of before Wednesday), but I would<br>
have to ask one major question: did the authors do a good job of researching<br>
their material or did they quote out of context to prove their point?<br>
We'll see what a rise out of the general congregation this will provide,<br>
though it seems that there were more important questions at the moment.<br>
<p>
One of the members reported of one member who has been publicly blasting<br>
the church. She suggested that we recommend that that member be removed<br>
from the rolls. Another member spoke, "If we did that to every member who<br>
puts down the church, we wouldn't have many church members left."<br>
<p>
******************************************************************************<br>
--Stan Macasieb (macasib@motcid.rtsg.mot.com)| <br>
