Here in Finland we do not generally have Sabbathproblems, but the devil is workin<br>
in more subtle ways. In Finland there is not free Saturdays but a five day<br>
week. That means that if there is a public holiday in the middle of the <br>
week, then you have to work that day in on Saturday, this will happen a couple<br>
times a year. When you are baptised then the problem with the sabbath is very <br>
far a way, and you do not want to embarass yourself and your boss with<br>
this matter. So when this Sabbbath comes, you are missing many of our<br>
"younger in spirit" member in the church.<br>
<p>
generally there are no schools on Saturdays, but now the government has<br>
decided that the spring feast at the end of the school year is always on saturday [K<br>
also the Christmas feast are quite often on saturdays.  And so it is not<br>
really school, so why not be there in stead for making big fuss...<br>
<p>
<p>
I think these Sabath problems are much bigger than when I had to<br>
make a decision here and now.<br>
<p>
RSi<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
