<title>Dec_1992: Positive effects of tithe loss &amp; recession to the Church</title>
<h1>Positive effects of tithe loss &amp; recession to the Church</h1>
Raylene (<i>CHRMD@cc.newcastle.edu.au</i>)<br>
<i>21 Dec 1992 09:39:06 +1100</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#97">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#97">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#97">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#97">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0098.html">Steven Timm: "Talking heads"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0096.html">Steven Timm: "Stephen Hawking and SDA's"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
cheryl berthelsen writes:<br>
<p>
<i>&gt;Now this I don't understand.  Is the ONLY evangelistic outreach in the SDA</i><br>
<i>&gt;church that of tithe-paid evangelists hired by the Church hierarchy?  I don't</i><br>
<i>&gt;think this was ever the PRIMARY mode of evangelism propagated by EGW.  In</i><br>
<i>&gt;fact, personal evangelism has ALWAYS been the most successful.  Is the</i><br>
<i>&gt;evangelistic outreach of the SDA church REALLY crippled by these lost funds?</i><br>
<i>&gt;Or is it a fact that so little of the tithe money goes for this purpose that</i><br>
<i>&gt;now they've budgetted it out?  (Of course, the Division wouldn't think of</i><br>
<i>&gt;trimming church hierarchy instead!  Having a top-heavy organization is</i><br>
<i>&gt;more important than evangelism?)</i><br>
<p>
It is my feeling that the financial difficulties of the Church come not just<br>
as a curse, but also as a blessing in disguise. Due to shortness of funds,<br>
the church in many areas is having to reexamine its priorities, and <br>
restructure its activities. Some really good things are resulting. (It almost<br>
makes me wonder whether people should have got together and deprived the<br>
Church of money a while back!!)(Well...maybe not!)<br>
<p>
It is hearing of this new-found flexibility (which I hope will spread) that<br>
encourages me about the church. It doesn't *have* to be stuck in a rut.<br>
<p>
Raylene<br>
---*---<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
