<!-- body="start" -->
Raylene made the comment that perhaps financial difficulty is good for the <br>
church sometimes because it forces innovation to occor which would not<br>
otherwise occur.  The present system of "departments" in the church<br>
organization was started because of necessity in the fields of South<br>
Africa<br>
and Australia in the late 1890's, and then was adopted by the whole church.<br>
<p>
But I do not agree that the church is currently in financial difficulty.<br>
The financial report as summarized in the Adventist Review indicates that<br>
fiscal 1992 was a good year for the church with record amounts of tithe<br>
and an operating surplus.  It makes me wonder if all this worry about <br>
"independent ministries" is just crying "Wolf!" when no wolf is around.<br>
<p>
Steve Timm<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
