<!-- body="start" -->
re. "independent ministries"  The G.C. has come down very hard on some<br>
of these lately.  INMHO it is SOLELY because they have accepted, and are<br>
soliciting tithe money.  I firmly believe that a person should be able<br>
to chose where his tithe money is used.  Personally, mine goes through<br>
normal church channels, though after reading the scathing reveiw article,<br>
and reading the official statement, I am sorely tempted to send a note<br>
to the G.C. telling them that I am withdrawing my tithe from normal church<br>
channels, and directing it toward the "independent ministries" because of<br>
thier attitude.  Personally, I enjoy reading Our Firm Foundation.  I don't<br>
think that the church as apostitized.  I don't agree with the brethern that<br>
the independent ministries call anything that they don't agree with apostacy.<br>
<p>
Most of the points held by the "independent ministries" have bee espoused at<br>
one time or other by the Adventist Church.  We have studiouly avoided adopting<br>
a creed, on Mrs. Whites council, and I think it should stay that way.  I see<br>
the churches paper and stance as a move toward establishing such a creed.<br>
(i.e.  If you aren't a loyal tither, who sends his tithe through church<br>
channels, then you can't be a Seventh-day Adventist.)<br>
Cheers<br>
Woody<br>
