<title>Dec_1992: Can visitors find your church in the phone book?</title>
<h1>Can visitors find your church in the phone book?</h1>
Steven Timm (<i>st0o+@andrew.cmu.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Fri,  1 Jan 1993 23:48:19 -0500 (EST)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#105">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#105">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#105">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#105">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0104.html">Raylene: "Re: Financial status and mixed blessings"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
In my recent travels in San Francisco, I was looking for a Seventh-day<br>
Adventist church in the San Francisco phone book.  I found only several<br>
congregations at which it was clear foreign tongues would be spoken.<br>
If I had not remembered a feature I had seen some time back, I wouldn't<br>
have thought to look under "Central" and thus successfully find the<br>
"Central Seventh-day Adventist Church", listed under "Central" in the<br>
phone book.  <br>
<p>
In Pittsburgh the Shadyside church is listed under "Seventh-day Adventist<br>
church in pages both white and yellow, this leads to us getting many of the <br>
visitors which come through town.  Is your church locatable in the phone<br>
book?  What about the hotel church directories?<br>
<p>
Just a thought.<br>
<p>
Steve Timm<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
