  Just received my gift subscription to Signs.  My wife's, sister's,<br>
husband's mother sent it to us (for some reason she had the card telling<br>
us it was coming say that it was from the sister-in-law?).<br>
<p>
  I see that this is published by the SDA church, so it is an official<br>
type of thing, right?  If it is in one of the articles then most of the<br>
mainstream SDA believe that?<br>
<p>
  More on my impressions of the magazine later.<br>
<p>
Scott       | No success can compensate for failure in the home. David O. McKay<br>
Mattes      | President 1951-70, Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-Day Saints<br>
[Signs of the Times is an official magazine of the SDA church and is its<br>
prime vehicle in North America for expounding its doctrine in a magazine.<br>
You are correct to consider it as representative of the mainstream.<br>
Hope you enjoy it.  If others are interested, I can post a subscription<br>
address, usually it is possible for non-members to get it free for a year.<br>
SCT]<br>
