<title>Feb_1992: How Adventists Can Stop Growing</title>
<h1>How Adventists Can Stop Growing</h1>
Steven Timm (<i>st0o+@andrew.cmu.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Fri, 14 Feb 1992 10:47:47 -0500 (EST)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#100">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#100">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#100">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#100">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0101.html">Steven Timm: "Re: EGW and perfection."</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0099.html">Kenroy: "Re: New networkers list"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
To Steve &amp;/or SDAnet<br>
<p>
I recently received a copy of an article that appeared in "Adventists<br>
Affirm", Spring 1991.  Titled "How Adventists Can Stop Growing", by<br>
Dean M. Kelley, Exec director for Religious Liberty National Council of<br>
Churches; the author of "Why Conservative Churches Are Growing.  The<br>
article had originally printed in "Ministry", Feb 1982.<br>
<p>
I could:<br>
<p>
  * Type it up for SDAnet.<br>
<p>
  * Type it up with lots of . . . . . . . to shorten it up, but retain<br>
    pretty much the message and words of the author.<br>
<p>
  * Resort to saying much of it in my own words, quoting here and there.<br>
<p>
Do you have a problem with entirely, or mostly quoting an article such<br>
as this?  In other words, what copy right rules apply?  Would something<br>
'copied' to SDAnet be construed as "publishing"?  Is SDAnet considered<br>
a publication?  I don't think so.<br>
<p>
Perhaps this was something already discussed on SDAnet when it came out?<br>
If its ancient history on this newsgroup then I'll not bring it back to<br>
the table.<br>
<p>
Dave (David E. Buxton)<br>
[As far as copyright laws are concerned, I think it technically is illegal<br>
to transmit a whole article across the net without the author's permission.<br>
But we have done this several times before, and I leave this to the <br>
discretion of the individual poster.  If you wish to avoid the appearance <br>
of evil, summarize the article.  I think it would be a good thing to discuss,<br>
we certainly have not discussed such an article here before.  SCT]<br>
<p>
<p>
----------------<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
