<title>Feb_1992: Pastors, etc.</title>
<h1>Pastors, etc.</h1>
Paul Gates (<i>70516.420@compuserve.com</i>)<br>
<i>07 Feb 92 21:44:13 EST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#79">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#79">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#79">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#79">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0080.html">Paul Gates: "Re: Pastors who seem uncommitted"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0078.html">Ruben Gonzalez: "Subject: Re: EGW and perfection."</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
The only thing I would say is that please do not put all SDA pastors in<br>
the one mold! I do not maintain a church office in the church that is. <br>
Through the years consistently I have driven 25,000 30,000 miles  a<br>
year. My work day usually consists of 15-16 hours. I am usually up by<br>
5:30 AM and many days do not get to bed till late. I am not lazy and I<br>
do produce along with visiting etc. I belong to 2 ministerial<br>
associations and do not know any Methodist,Baptist, Presbyterian, <br>
Catholic, or independent ministries that  do the visiting that I do.<br>
<p>
I believe perhaps that you are talking about big city church pastors<br>
perhaps. The problem with the Adventist ministries if there is a<br>
problem is that too much is expected of us out of the real ministry. <br>
By that I mean correspondence, paper work, Administration. I do not<br>
have any kind of a secretary or secretarial help.<br>
<p>
Please do not put all of us in one pot. We just do not fit!<br>
<p>
&lt;&lt;Paul&gt;&gt;<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
