  If anyone is interested, there is an INTERNET site that specializes in<br>
sharing veggie recipes.  The address is<br>
<p>
  "GRANOLA: Vegetarian Discussion List" &lt;GRANOLA@brownvm.brown.edu&gt;<br>
<p>
  To sign up, send a mail item with the command "SUB GRANOLA your name"<br>
as the text of the message to LISTSERV@BROWNVM.BROWN.EDU.  Do not<br>
include the " marks in the "SUB" command you send.<br>
<p>
  If you would like the recipes that I have extracted from their log<br>
files you can FTP to me at 144.11.100.1, userid ANONYMOU, password GUEST<br>
and get the 4 files VEGGIE RECIPESx, where x is the number 1 to 4.<br>
Also, I have a separate file of food information from the same place, it<br>
is called VEGGIE FOODINFO.<br>
<p>
  All the files are less than 220k.<br>
<p>
  If you would like the files, and don't have FTP, write me and ask.<br>
