<!-- body="start" -->
Hi, new SDA-L people.<br>
 <br>
My name is Steve Timm and I'm the moderator of SDAnet, the Seventh-day<br>
Adventist discussion network.  When you post something to SDA-L, it<br>
automatically also goes out to the 80  or so subscribers of SDAnet.<br>
(But our posts are not echoed to SDA-L.)  If you were subscribed to<br>
SDAnet, you would have already received almost 100 messages this month.<br>
Our topics include some of the more volatile discussions in the SDA church<br>
today, which painful experience has taught us are best discussed on<br>
a moderated network such as SDAnet rather than an unmoderated list such<br>
as SDA-L.<br>
 <br>
If you are interested in more information on SDAnet, please drop me<br>
a line at<br>
 <br>
ST0O+SDA@ANDREW.Bitnet   or st0o+SDA@andrew.cmu.edu<br>
 <br>
I'm impressed that Christine tries to keep track of the names of everyone.<br>
There are some people that have been on my list for years that I still<br>
don't know their names.  But here is a list that comprises most of<br>
what I know about the SDAnet people.  Those with a semicolon (;)<br>
in front of the address are addresses that don't work anymore,<br>
or people that are temporarily inactive.<br>
 <br>
Steve Timm<br>
