<title>Feb_1992: Possibility of not sinning</title>
<h1>Possibility of not sinning</h1>
David Plaisted (<i>plaisted@cs.unc.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Mon, 10 Feb 92 17:20:36 -0500</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#87">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#87">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#87">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#87">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0088.html">Daniel D Deavours: "Re: EGW and perfection"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0086.html">Scott Mattes: "Growth of SDA church"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
I know that when I was first becoming a Seventh-day Adventist, the<br>
possibility of not sinning was a new thought to me, and made a<br>
deep impression on me.  The same thing happened to a friend of mine<br>
when I explained this to him.  He felt like it gave him some hope,<br>
that he didn't have to keep on sinning and failing.  I think that<br>
we are really missing a powerful message by ignoring the Scriptural<br>
evidence and the testimony of Ellen White and Jones and Waggoner<br>
on this topic, which I believe to be part of the message that the<br>
Lord has given to this church for the last days.<br>
<p>
	Dave Plaisted<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
