<!-- body="start" -->
Dave, I may be completing missing your thought. My main point is that<br>
our main focus should not be on sinlessness and perfection. My main<br>
focus should be on Jesus Christ and what he can do for us.<br>
<p>
It would be for instance like making the focal point of Adventism, the<br>
Sabbath, or our teaching of the "State of the Dead" rather than on<br>
accepting Jesus Christ first and his righteousness. In my life I am<br>
counting on Jesus Christ through the Holy Spirit to take care of the<br>
sinlessness and perfection in my life and I am satisfied that He is<br>
doing it!<br>
<p>
&lt;&lt;Paul&gt;&gt;<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
