Steve,  (You do not have to post this on the SDA net, use your own<br>
judgement).<br>
<p>
My experience with churches and members through the years has indicated<br>
to me that a large section of Adventists vote Republican. However, it<br>
seems that not considering religious affliations, that Democrats are<br>
more supportive to our Religious Liberty ideals.<br>
<p>
We, Evelyn and I, have not had religious affliations and religious<br>
views high on our priorities, in fact not even a priority. We have<br>
tried to make our decision on the candidates in their abilities to<br>
accomplish what we feel is needful for our country. Perhaps religious<br>
views should play a larger role in our decisions.<br>
<p>
I think Bush has a uphill battle ahead of him. BTW, to help you<br>
understand better our disregard of religious affliation, -- Once in<br>
Fla. in a state election one of the candidates obtained a mailing list<br>
of all the SDA members in Fla and wrote them to vote for him that he<br>
was in favor of their beliefs especially on Rel. Lib, etc. <br>
<p>
My dad had dinner with the other candidate and found out the other<br>
candidate was in just as much favor as the other one. Just because a<br>
candidate is catholic or jesuite does not necessarily mean they will be<br>
trouble for SDAs. It depends on the individual and their own personal<br>
views. <br>
<p>
Why don't you contact Gary Ross at the GC. Their phone number is <br>
301-680-6000 I believe. Gary is the Liason between the GC and<br>
Congress. He might have some info. If I would have known last week, <br>
Gary Ross preached at our church and had a RL rally in the afternoon.<br>
<p>
Take care,<br>
<p>
&lt;&lt;Paul&gt;&gt;<br>
