<title>Feb_1992: politics and religious liberty</title>
<h1>politics and religious liberty</h1>
McCluskey G (<i>glenm@usl.com</i>)<br>
<i>Fri, 21 Feb 92 11:12:21 EST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#115">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#115">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#115">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#115">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0116.html">Mark T Brower: "Re: How Adventism Can Stop Growing"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0114.html">Dave Buxton: "Re: Presidential Politics and Religious Liberty"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
Content-Type: text<br>
Content-Length: 1259<br>
<p>
<i>&gt; My experience with churches and members through the years has</i><br>
<i>&gt; indicated to me that a large section of Adventists vote Republican.</i><br>
<i>&gt; However, it seems that not considering religious affliations, that</i><br>
<i>&gt; Democrats are more supportive to our Religious Liberty ideals.</i><br>
<p>
I am not sure this is the place to debate the merits and demerits of<br>
our two main political parties.  A couple of points, however.<br>
<p>
1.  Republicans tend to favor issues like support for private schools,<br>
religious displays in public places, and so on.  Religious liberty<br>
advocates wring their hands over these items.<br>
<p>
2.  Democrats favor big government and intrusion into people's lives.<br>
Religious liberty advocates don't wring their hands about this but<br>
they should, since the threat is the same or worse as that from<br>
Republicans.<br>
<p>
3.  Libertarians really do want government out of people's lives and<br>
thus from a pure religious liberty standpoint are preferable to the<br>
other parties.  However, if you want government that has "values" and<br>
is "moral", Libertarians are not the way to go.<br>
<p>
4.  Religous liberty advocates have never solved the problem<br>
highlighted in point #3.  It is hard for a government to have values<br>
without having a basis for those values.<br>
<p>
Glen McCluskey<br>
glenm@usl.com<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
