<!-- body="start" -->
Lola, How abt small group ministries? I think particularly in large<br>
churches like the Hope church -- where is it -- Oregon? has good success<br>
with Small Groups.<br>
<p>
Another thing to consider is whenever a new church organizes there always<br>
is a lot of fervor, and "on fire."  You have to develop a church plan to<br>
keep that fervor going. I was pastor in a church for 8 years and that is a<br>
long time for a SDA pastorate. Every year we had a new program going on<br>
and helped the people develop their spiritual gifts. During those 8 years<br>
the people never did lose their high spirit and fervor.<br>
<p>
The church was without a pastor for 6 months after I left. You would have<br>
never known there was not a pastor because the laity were carrying the<br>
ball as they had been trained to do so. I am not suggesting Lola, that<br>
"plans" are a Saviour. However, you do need a plan! It is good to have a<br>
1, 3, and 5 year plan and plans so you know where you are headed and what<br>
your goals are.<br>
<p>
&lt;&lt;Paul&gt;&gt;<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
