Very good thoughts, Steve. While I was reading your messages I was<br>
thinking about 2 congregations that are having outstanding growth and are<br>
pastored by lay people who have other full time jobs. You could conclude I<br>
suppose from that, that pastors stiffle growth!! Not really, these two<br>
churches are new churches -- people really active -- and right along with<br>
that they have some laity "spark plugs" that really get the people going<br>
in the right direction.<br>
<p>
Ray &amp; Madalyn Hamblin in Adrian/Tecumseh, Mich. are like that. They both<br>
were and still are spark plugs in the Adrian church. Ray can really<br>
challenge the members and they are ready the follow him and the pastor. <br>
It was thrilling to be their pastor. While I was there with God's blessing<br>
we not only increased the membership in Adrian but planted a new church <br>
in Tecumseh. Dr Gordon Guild and his wife Carol are also spark plugs in<br>
the Tecumseh church.<br>
<p>
Ray is the national president of ASI now. He owns Hamblin Printing Co. in<br>
Tecumseh. He has done some of my printing that we have inserted in the<br>
local newspapers. We went from churches that had no interest names at all<br>
to over 500 names in our files at present. Over half of them have<br>
requested Bible studies and we are actively and have been actively<br>
following them up. In addition to that we  have many who have requested<br>
other seminars that we conduct each year.<br>
<p>
The answer is to equip the saints so that they can work in concert with<br>
the pastor.<br>
<p>
&lt;&lt;Paul&gt;&gt;<br>
