<title>Feb_1993: Re: The "Sharing Scripture" SS lesson</title>
<h1>Re: The "Sharing Scripture" SS lesson</h1>
April Grabast (<i>grabast@edmund.cs.andrews.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Tue, 23 Feb 1993 16:45:44 -0500 (EST)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#222">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#222">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#222">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#222">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0223.html">PHTH1@cc.newcastle.edu.au: "Food laws"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0221.html">Sherman Cox: "Re: The "Sharing Scripture" SS lesson"</a>
<li> <b>In reply to:</b> <a href="0218.html">Steven Timm: "The "Sharing Scripture" SS lesson"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
While vacationing this past summer I was involved in a Sabbath School<br>
Class which used sharing scripture.  The people were ages 20 to about 35<br>
or 40.  The discussion was alive, real, honest and personel.  I was<br>
impressed by the whole experience.  I did not get a chance to talk with<br>
the leader and therefore did not find out where the lessons might be<br>
obtained.  I would be appreciative if you could share this information!<br>
We need lesson helps that will help us be relevant to our relationships<br>
with others and assist us in being transparent and honest about our own<br>
shortcomings.  How else do we grow?!<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
