<!-- body="start" -->
In the past few years there has been a new type of Sabbath School lesson<br>
that is geared at relational Bible study.  It comes as a discussion guide<br>
and usually just comprises the front and back of one sheet of paper.<br>
Included in it are some key texts, and several discussion scenarios.<br>
It's called "Sharing Scripture."  I don't know where it is available from <br>
but can find out if needed, since my mother writes for them regularly.<br>
<p>
Has anyone out there used this lesson?  What are your experiences with it,<br>
if so?<br>
<p>
Steve Timm<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
