Given Ruben's comments on the state of affairs here in Australia, I feel<br>
myself fortunate to have grown up as a missionaries' child in other Pacific<br>
countries (specifically New Zealand and Papua New Guinea). I also feel<br>
blessed to have had parents who made it their responsibility to teach me<br>
about God and about the Adventist church, incdluding SDA church history<br>
and distinctive beliefs.<br>
<p>
It seems remarkable that so many Adventist ministers and parents are<br>
shirking their God-given responsibility here in Australia, if what Ruben<br>
says is indeed the case. Are there any other net readers who are familiar<br>
with the Australian branch of the church who would be prepared to offer an<br>
opinion on this?<br>
<p>
