Hi all,<br>
<p>
<p>
	Let me say that Sherman's quote of mine regarding the Australian<br>
situation was not meant for public dissemination. It was in a private<br>
email message to Sherman.<br>
<p>
I realise Sherman mistook my private message as being an SDAnet message<br>
which does occur sometimes and therefore replied publicly. <br>
<p>
However now that it has been published, let me just qualify it by saying<br>
that I do not wish to imply that *all* the youth are like this. Neither was<br>
I reflecting either directly nor indirectly on the Australian contributors<br>
to SDAnet, since I don't believe they fall into this category. However it<br>
is my sad oppinion that the majority of SDA youth that I do personally know<br>
(and are not subscribers to SDAnet) are this way. <br>
<p>
To attempt to qualify this I'm not sure what the exact numbers are (70% ?)<br>
[ help me out here if the figure is wrong ]<br>
but most of the SDA youth leave the church just after graduating from<br>
high school. From my very own class at high school I would say that<br>
most no longer attend church, in fact the church membership in Sydney<br>
is actually decreasing, if one does not consider the stabilising effect<br>
of the ethinc work. In fact I am deeply concerned regarding the future of the <br>
church here in Sydney because of this very problem.<br>
<p>
I appologise if any were led to a wrong conclusion, or if this issue caused any<br>
to receive a wrong impression regarding any Australian contributors to SDAnet.<br>
<p>
<p>
Sincerely,<br>
Ruben.<br>
