<title>Feb_1993: How about a new more acurate translation then</title>
<h1>How about a new more acurate translation then</h1>
Russell Yonkers (<i>ryonkers@mis.mi04.zds.com</i>)<br>
<i>Wed, 3 Feb 93 8:29:27 EST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#22">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#22">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#22">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#22">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0023.html">Steven Timm: "More on Bible translations"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0021.html">Warren C Trenchard: "On the Text of the New Testament"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
<li> <b>Next in thread:</b> <a href="0067.html">Woody Baker: "Re: How about a new more acurate translation then"</a>
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
I Think that it is interesting that no one has made the additional and most<br>
obvious suggestion to clear up most of this debate.  If the MMS that were<br>
used for the KJV are so accurate then why do we not take those same MMS<br>
and re-translate them into modern english.  We do not live in the 1600's<br>
and most people do not understand 17th century english.  Thus it seems <br>
that the greatest service to mankind would be to re-translate the scriptures<br>
using the original MSS that are to be found the most accurate.<br>
<p>
One other point that I would like to make is in response to something that <br>
Ruben said.  He said that the fact that the newer translations are copyrighted<br>
is proof that they are man's work and not God's Word.  This is absurd.  The <br>
only reason that the KJV is not copyrighted is due to it's age (it is out of<br>
the period of copyright).  The reason that the other translations are copyrighted<br>
is to protect the investment made in time and money to have the translations<br>
made.  This was done at great expense ot the companies involved and they<br>
need to try to protect thier investment so that they can make a profit and <br>
stay afloat.  These are produced by companies that need to make money.  They <br>
are not produced by the government that can just steal from us to pay its bill.<br>
And there is nothing wrong with being a company for profit.  Drug companies<br>
have the same protection as far as patents on new drugs that are put on the <br>
market.  How else are we going to afford new research and new products.  And<br>
the scripture quoted is a perfect example of what people right here on SDAnet<br>
call using the scripture as a club to fit your own purposes.  <br>
<p>
Don't mean to be so pointed but I really felt that needed to be said.  I hope <br>
that we can all continue to discuss this sensitive topic without building <br>
up any animosity.<br>
<p>
YHS Russell<br>
