I have a view on this copywrite issue of bibles and EGW.  I feel that <br>
to give controling power to a commitee to make sure that scripture and EGW <br>
are not slandered, taken way out of contect, and such.  Say for example. <br>
If I was very mad at the church I could take scripture and say something<br>
like, "I say Christ, I will not come to get you again." and then list lots<br>
of verses where I have cut and paste...  But that is a poor example.  I do<br>
think Bible quotation should be monitored for proper use so that we don't <br>
make it say things it doesn't.  But at free cost.<br>
<p>
Maybe I am strange.  But I am for Copywriting everything writen by any<br>
one.  This gives legal support for rights.  Do you want Satan to try to<br>
have so one print a, "Good News Bible" and have it full of new age info? <br>
That would be a violation of a copywrited title.  We could stop the<br>
production of such.  <br>
<p>
Just my ideas..<br>
<p>
<p>
Scott Bechtel<br>
