<i>&gt; A note to Ruben.  The Reina y Valera you find so accurate is a Catholic </i><br>
<i>&gt; translation.  Not until the 1960 version sponsored by the International Bible </i><br>
<i>&gt; Society did protestants have much say other than in leaving out the Apocrypha </i><br>
<i>&gt; in their printings.</i><br>
<p>
I never said it was very accurate, I just said that one main error which<br>
attacked SDA doctrine was to be found in Hebrews, I am aware it is a Catholic <br>
translation. There is no equivalent to the KJV in Spanish but if one had<br>
to be found the Reina y Valera version from 1601 would have to count<br>
due to its language and age.<br>
