<i>&gt;&gt;&gt; Item number 1280, dated 92/02/23 21:45:08 -- ALL</i><br>
======================================================================== 19<br>
<p>
*From:         Eric Thomas &lt;ERIC@SEARN.BITNET&gt;<br>
*Subject:      Re: Being moderator from VMS or Unix systems<br>
*Date:         Sun, 23 Feb 1992 21:45:08 +0100<br>
*In-Reply-To:  Message of Sun,<br>
<p>
LISTSERV wants you to forward  the message using the 'Resent-' mechanism,<br>
which the Internet un*x people designed and documented for the purpose of<br>
then not using  it when they wrote mail programs.  The original header is<br>
kept as is, and  the user interface adds a set of  'Resent-' tags for the<br>
new message.  You can't get VMSmail  to do that because  it knows nothing<br>
about RFC822. Maybe ELM has some switch that will make it do that.<br>
<p>
  Eric<br>
<p>
