<p>
*From:         Eric Thomas &lt;ERIC@SEARN.BITNET&gt;
*Subject:      Re: How to manage a LISTSERV list from a UNIX machine?
*Date:         Fri, 18 Jan 91 19:50:42 +0100
<p>
On Fri, 18 Jan 91 12:47:03 CST Alfredo Delgado Garza
&lt;adelgado@MTECV2.MTY.ITESM.MX&gt; said:
&gt;But I  want to be  able to  make modifications to  the list from  a UNIX
&gt;internet only machine.
<p>
You can't.  In the  next version  you'll be  able to  do a  'GET listname
(HEADER' to retrieve  just the header. You can then  extract it, edit it,
and PUT it back.  Again, this does NOT work with 1.6e;  do NOT attempt to
send back just the header, it would delete all the subscribers.
<p>
  Eric
<p>
&gt;&gt;&gt; Item number 65, dated 91/01/18 13:54:00 -- ALL
======================================================================== 24
<p>
*From:         Joe McMahon &lt;XRJDM@SCFVM.BITNET&gt;
*Subject:      Re: How to manage a LISTSERV list from a UNIX machine?
*Date:         Fri, 18 Jan 91 13:54:00 EST
*In-Reply-To:  Message of Fri,
<p>
I've done this when our BITNet link to AU was down, but our Internet
connection was up. You just need to send mail to the LISTSERV rather
than trying to send messages.
<p>
Make sure that the "Owner=" is set to the Internet address from which
you'll be mailing commands. BITnet user who have access both ways can
add both their BITNet and Internet IDs:
<p>
Owner=XRJDM@SCFVM,xrjdm@scfvm.gsfc.nasa.gov
<p>
I believe there's a "QUIET" option that can keep one of the two
aliases from getting messages.
<p>
 --- Joe M.
