Ah finally the folks at the University of Leiden admit to having problems.
<p>
Probably it's unrelated to the UCX problem, but the machine
rulway.LeidenUniv.nl
is definitely wrongly configured.  That's the next hop from Ryko's machine.
I recall an excellent (what else !) explanation from Ned recently what causes
the symptoms described below.
<p>
Rulway.LeidenUniv.nl has been bouncing *vast* amounts of mail from our Netserv
with the beautiful Unuchs error message :
<p>
&lt;&lt;&lt; 553 rulway.LeidenUniv.nl I refuse to talk to myself
554 &lt;WMBKARRE@rulgl.LeidenUniv.nl&gt;... Service unavailable: Bad file number
<p>
Ned's explanation of that was that the machine doesn't know its own name :-)
<p>
Mx records for the LeidenUniv.NL domain point (amongst others) to rulway
so I suggest you get that machine fixed as the first step in trying to
locate the problems.
<p>
Btw.  I may be slightly biased, but I get the impression that an awfully
high percentage of Unix sendmail configurations are broken ... I'd be
interested in hearing other PostMasters' experience.
