I'm on a Unix machine in Mississippi, running WORDS-L on a VM system
in Georgia.  Before the new version of listserv, I had to use bitnet
to get and put the list headers.  (I would get the file interactively,
then put it back with the 'netcopy' command.)  Now that it's possible
to get the headers only, I do everything by internet mail.  I get
the headers by sending this command to the listserv:
get words-l (header
And I mail it back to the listserv.  It works fine.
   --Natalie (nm1@ra.msstate.edu)
