<title>Feb_1993: who I am</title>
<h1>who I am</h1>
Russell Yonkers (<i>ryonkers@mis.mi04.zds.com</i>)<br>
<i>Thu, 4 Feb 93 8:18:00 EST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#42">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#42">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#42">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#42">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0043.html">Russell Yonkers: "Ruben, commandment keeping and just. by faith"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0041.html">David E. Johnson: "More on Bible translations"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
After I saw the post by my good friend Andy Arkusinski telling about himself<br>
I decided it was time for me to do the same.  I used to go to church in the <br>
Wyoming SDA church with Andy and Holly until we moved from Grand Rapids to <br>
Stevensville, MI (next to Berrien Springs the heart of the Adventist holy<br>
land ((tongue in cheek))).  I work for Zenith Data Systems as a LAN           <br>
administrator.  I am a Novell CNE and am learning Unix by immersion (just<br>
throw me in and I will either sink or swim).  <br>
<p>
I am married and have 5 kids with another on the way.  Currently 2 boys and<br>
3 girls (of course we are hoping for another boy). My wife is a musician.<br>
Karen (my wife) spent 4 years at Hope college as a music major and was only<br>
a year away from finishing when I swept her away to married life (it was a <br>
5 year degree program).  She still keeps in music in the church.  My life <br>
centers around my family and my computer.  I am learning programing right now<br>
(dBase, Quickbasic, and Toolbook for MS Windows) and hope to go back to school<br>
soon to get a degree in computer science (where I am sure that I will be   <br>
introduced to the joys of C programming!).  <br>
<p>
One last thing.  Andy forgot to mention in his that he plays a mean trumpet<br>
and baritone.  I know these things because he has played in groups with <br>
my wife.<br>
<p>
Well gotta run now.  Time to make those big bucks just to send them <br>
all to Slick Wille (opps I promised my wife I would be nicer to him)<br>
to President Clinton (America held hostage, day _).<br>
<p>
YHS Russell<br>
