<title>Feb_1993: Re: pregnant teens</title>
<h1>Re: pregnant teens</h1>
Scott  Bechtel (<i>srbechte@nyx.cs.du.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Thu, 4 Feb 93 22:40:33 MST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#56">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#56">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#56">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#56">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0057.html">davidbu@loowit.wr.tek.com: "Multiple Scheloris and Diet"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0055.html">Warren C Trenchard: "The Text for the Last Time"</a>
<li> <b>In reply to:</b> <a href="0048.html">Fred Christiansen: "pregnant teens"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
Fred,<br>
I stongly agree with your stance on supporting people with love what have <br>
not fully fallowed God's word.  We all have fallen at one time or another.<br>
We are all sinners and only through Christ can we be saved and helped to<br>
over come those disires.  So with this in mine I think that it is so<br>
stupid the way people are so judgmental about fornication.  I feel sex<br>
sters people up more than any other topic!  (Probibly out of guilt at<br>
times)  <br>
<p>
What makes fornication any diffrent than any other sin?  So why don't<br>
people accept them as they do other sinners and help them stay in God's<br>
hospital called the "church"?<br>
<p>
I have come from a conservitive home.  SDA all my life.  I am currently a<br>
first year student at Union and am takeing Theology and Business Adm.  But<br>
that does not change my nature.  <br>
<p>
Though Chirst all things are posible.  I agree that through Christ we can<br>
help to suppress a lot of sexual thoughts and desires.  By focusing time<br>
on God rather than pornographic material.  But at the same time when you <br>
get into a relationship that changes really quick.  You let your hormons<br>
take over and don't keep God in your heart.  At least in many cases, such<br>
as the one I just got out of a week ago.  If you had asked me at<br>
Christmass time if I thought fornication was wrong.  I would have said,<br>
Biblicly yes.  But if asked if I would have sex out side of marriage I<br>
would have again answered yes.  Just because person knows something is<br>
wrong, doesn't mean that they are allowing Christ to work.  It usely means<br>
that they are letting their bodys control themselves.<br>
<p>
I have found a text in 1 Thes. 4:3 ". . . that you should avoid sexual<br>
immorality; that each of you should learn to control his own body...."<br>
NIV<br>
<p>
This text I feel shoud be the whole key to the SDA aproch to teaching<br>
youth aobut sexuality and control.  As I have strugled with the temptation<br>
of having sex I have come to realize that today there are two extreams. <br>
1. the TV and secular socity says that it's ok to have sex.  Just have<br>
safer sex.  (or they say that if you decide too, than use this...  good..<br>
but gives the impression of permition.)  and 2.  A very legalistic stance<br>
by most churches saying not to have sex.  <br>
<p>
As I strugled through the Bible on this and lots of prayer, I came to a<br>
conclution.  That even thought God says no I was going to go ahaid and do<br>
it any ways.  (Through discutions with my girlfriend at the time, we<br>
decided not to...  How I hated it then!  But now I'm still wishing we had.<br>
 But I'm sure when I get maried I will be glad that I waited!  But for<br>
now--my hormons are still yelling at me...)  I FELT THAT SINCE I COULDN'T<br>
FIND ANY WAYS IN THE BIBLE TO TURN OFF 100% THAT TEMPTATION AND A WAY FOR<br>
GOD TO TURN OFF HORMONS THROUGH PRAYER, THAT I WAS GOING TO BE SELFISH AND<br>
DO IT ANY WAYS.  <br>
<p>
I am still very torn on this issue!!!!  I feel that the SDA church really<br>
needs to teach  youth how to control their bodies.  The text says to, so<br>
how do we?  (for me I started using a medication for a rash in a location<br>
south of my belly butten and found that it helped to cool things off for<br>
many hours:)  I have often thought of asking the doctor for a medication<br>
to turn of my sexual drive....:)   But through continual focus on God and<br>
from doing his service we can over come this nagging problem.  BUT!  Youth<br>
need hard answers!  ( I have alwasy heard the birds and the bees and then<br>
I heard aobut conterceptives.  And you hear about the results of having<br>
sex--unwanted pregnancy.  But you never really hear about how to control<br>
our bodys (they say well don't get into that situation where you will want<br>
to make out..  that is good--but to make the decition to be in that place<br>
you have already decided what you are wanting to do.  it must come before<br>
that.))  <br>
<p>
As many might tell.  This is a very strong issue for me.  I am trying to<br>
lead a life of God.  Since Chirstmass I have asked God to forgive my<br>
stupidness for out right wanting to ignor His commands.  But I still<br>
haven't found 100% of the answers.    (maybe about50% though:)    <br>
<p>
With TV, and our hormons, God is hard to hear.  Today people need to hear<br>
firm principles of how to have a continual relationship with God, basicly<br>
a courtship, to have as our shield and mastor Chimist.<br>
<p>
Last week when I broke up--sex was the last thing on earth I wanted.  Yet<br>
tonight I was having a discution about condoms and such with a friend of<br>
mine that is a female.  How quickly Satan can break back in!<br>
<p>
<p>
Legalizem and secularism won't work to fight Satan or sexual temptation. <br>
Only a ballenced life in the service of God.  But that is so hard to live!<br>
<p>
<p>
<p>
