<!-- body="start" -->
A friend of ours has recently been diagnosed as having Multiple Scheloris.<br>
I'd guess she is in her 50s or early 60s.<br>
She had been to a lot of doctors because of her symptoms, finally<br>
referred to the top M.S. doctor in the NW.  MRI scans etc and its<br>
now confirmed.<br>
<p>
Based on her history of symptoms, the doctor concluded that she has<br>
had it since childhood.  His question was: "you should be dead by now,<br>
what have you been eating?"   Her reply was that she has been a<br>
vegetarian since the age of 2.  He broke out into a broad smile,<br>
commenting that is the diet he puts his patients on.  He is not SDA.  <br>
She will be one of his special study cases to help confirm the doctors<br>
diet theories, especially with regards to vegies.<br>
<p>
DaveB<br>
