Well, well, for once I agree with Ruben on something!  I also do not<br>
think that people should get rich selling Bibles or any other article<br>
of religion.  Guess how this makes me feel about the way we run our<br>
literature evangelism work?  No, I realize that most L.E.s are not<br>
rich -- on the contrary, they sometimes are starving because they<br>
rely on commission and the books are so over-priced that almost nobody<br>
can afford to buy them anymore!  When will the higher-ups see that if<br>
we really want to spread the Good News, then we must make it affordable.<br>
I'm for putting L.E.s on salary and lowering the price of the books<br>
to within reach of at least the middle class, if not lower!<br>
<p>
Lola<br>
Aagaard@Morekypr<br>
