<title>Feb_1993: Ruben, commandment keeping and just. by faith</title>
<h1>Ruben, commandment keeping and just. by faith</h1>
Ruben Gonzalez (<i>ruben@ee.uts.edu.au</i>)<br>
<i>Mon, 8 Feb 93 12:09:18 EST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#70">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#70">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#70">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#70">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0071.html">CHRMD@cc.newcastle.edu.au: "Re: making money on religion"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0069.html">David Plaisted: "control of sex"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
<li> <b>Next in thread:</b> <a href="0077.html">Bruce Holm: "Re: Ruben, commandment keeping and just. by faith"</a>
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
Russell writes:<br>
<p>
<i>&gt; I was reading one of Rubens messages this morning and saw a very interesting</i><br>
<i>&gt; and troublesome point made.  This had to do with a verse that tells us that</i><br>
<i>&gt; we are only able to claim salvation by keeping the commandments. (This is a</i><br>
<i>&gt; paraphrase and if I am wrong feel free to correct me Ruben)  </i><br>
<p>
I have previously discussed this some time ago, and those who remember will <br>
know that this is not the case. I do not believe in salvation by works.<br>
<p>
Salvation is by faith alone, however faith = trust and obey. So that<br>
the saving faith is that faith that obeys. For this reason the translation<br>
of Rev 22:14 is correct because it exemplifies that type of faith necessary<br>
for salvation. For this very reason Rev 22:14 (KJV style) is unpopular<br>
with evangelicals.<br>
<p>
Ruben.<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
