<!-- body="start" -->
The question about Ellen White and prophecy points to a common misconception <br>
about prophecy. We tend to always think of prophecy in terms of prediction. If<br>
 <br>
one studies prophecy and prophets in scripture, I think you will find that <br>
prophets communicate messages from God to man. Many prophets never predicted <br>
anything. Predictions within prophecy come only as they relate to a specific <br>
message and usually in a conditional manner, i.e. if you don't change your <br>
course then this will be the result.<br>
 <br>
Ed Fargusson (Compuserve 72450,2430)<br>
<p>
Two points.  Some folk think prophets make only prophecies (predictions<br>
of the future); however, my understanding is that a prophet is one who<br>
has a message from God (which can include stuff about the future); and,<br>
yes, EGW did write a lot of what could be considered commentary.<br>
 <br>
Two, there's always the classic link between tobacco, certain foods,<br>
and cancer which she talked about years before it was accepted by<br>
the general population.<br>
<pre>
-- 
Fred Christiansen, Motorola, 2900 S Diablo Way, Tempe, AZ 85282  "Canajun, eh?
"
fredch@phx.mcd.mot.com  ||  uunet!phx.mcd.mot.com!fredch  ||  +1 602-438-3464
  ".. I have set before you Life and Death, blessing and cursing;  therefore
      choose Life, that both you and your children may live"  Deut 30:19
<p>
Excerpts from mail: 9-Feb-93  by TANG BENG YONG@nusunix2. 
&gt; 
&gt;Dear Link Hudson,
&gt; 
&gt;You said:
&gt; 
&gt;&gt;I have read that the SDA's consider Ellen G. White to be a prophetess.
&gt;&gt;Did she give any prophecies or just write Bible commentary. have any of her
&gt;&gt;prophecies come true?
&gt; 
&gt;&gt;Link Hudson.
&gt; 
&gt;     Well, first of all, we have to understand what a prophet is. 
&gt; 
&gt;THE MEANING OF "PROPHET"
&gt;------------------------
&gt;Nowadays, the word "prophet" connotes a person who foretells future events.
&gt;However, when used in the bible, it has a much broader meaning. The words
&gt;translated as  "prophet"  and  "prophetess"  in the bible, correspond to
&gt;the Hebrew words  "nabi"  and  "nebiah"  and to the Greek  "prophetes" 
&gt;and "prophetis" respectively. It denotes someone who has been specially
&gt;called by God, to speak on His behalf, to represent Him before His people
&gt;and to convey His messages, His will to them. The bible often says that
&gt;"the word of the LORD came to"  such and such a prophet and they usually
&gt;prefix their messages with a "Thus saith the LORD". (By contrast, the
&gt;main function of a priest is to represent the people before God).
&gt;     As such, although God often gives prophets messages to pass on to
&gt;people about future events, this is just part of their role, and perhaps
&gt;not even the main one at that. Of Moses, it is written:
&gt; 
&gt;     "And there arose not a prophet since in Israel like unto Moses,
&gt;      whom the LORD knew face to face," Deut 34:10
&gt; 
&gt;and yet the prediction of future events was a comparatively small part of
&gt;his function.
&gt; 
&gt;     And when he gave the excuse that he was too tongue-tied to speak to
&gt;pharaoh, God appointed Aaron to be Moses' spokesman, and this is how He
&gt;put it:
&gt; 
&gt;     "And the LORD said unto Moses, See, I have made thee a god to
&gt;      Pharaoh: and Aaron thy brother shall be thy prophet."
&gt;      Exod 7:1
&gt; 
&gt;So, Moses was the prophet of God and Aaron was the prophet of Moses in
&gt;this case. This gives us an idea of the meaning of the word.
&gt; 
&gt; 
&gt;DO SDAs CONSIDER ELLEN WHITE TO HAVE BEEN A PROPHETESS?
&gt;-------------------------------------------------------
&gt;     Now, how about Ellen G. White? Although she did not use the word
&gt;"prophet" to refer to herself, she did claim to have been given specific
&gt;messages from God to convey to the Seventh-day Adventist church mainly,
&gt;to the world at large also, and to certain individuals. This, together
&gt;with the fact that she possessed the characteristics given in the bible,
&gt;of a true prophet of God, has led to SDAs calling her a prophet.
&gt; 
&gt;THE TESTS OF A TRUE PROPHET
&gt;---------------------------
&gt;     The bible plainly states that there will be false teachers and false
&gt;prophets going around and deceiving people.  We all know that this is
&gt;nothing new. The question now is, how do you tell a true prophet from a
&gt;fake one?
&gt;     Time does not permit me to go into all of this in detail, if you're
&gt;interested, do let me know, and we can discuss it another time. Here is
&gt;just some of the guidelines about prophets from the bible:
&gt; 
&gt;Despise not prophesyings. Prove all things; hold fast that which is good.
&gt;Abstain from all appearance of evil. 1Thess 5:20-22
&gt; 
&gt;To the law and to the testimony: if they speak not according to this word,
&gt;it is because there is no light in them. Isa 8:20
&gt; 
&gt;Wherefore by their fruits ye shall know them. Matt 7:20
&gt; 
&gt;And he said, Hear now my words: If there be a prophet among you, I the LORD
&gt;will make myself known unto him in a vision, and will speak unto him in a
&gt;dream. Num 12:6
&gt; 
&gt;For the prophecy came not in old time by the will of man: but holy men of
&gt;God spake as they were moved by the Holy Ghost. 2Pe 1:21
&gt; 
&gt;Beloved, believe not every spirit, but try the spirits whether they are
&gt;of God: because many false prophets are gone out into the world. Hereby
&gt;know ye the Spirit of God: Every spirit that confesseth that Jesus Christ
&gt;is come in the flesh is of God: And every spirit that confesseth not that
&gt;Jesus Christ is come in the flesh is not of God: and this is that spirit
&gt;of antichrist, whereof ye have heard that it should come; and even now
&gt;already is it in the world. 1 Jn 4:1-3
&gt; 
&gt;If there arise among you a prophet, or a dreamer of dreams, and giveth
&gt;thee a sign or a wonder, And the sign or the wonder come to pass, whereof
&gt;he spake unto thee, saying, Let us go after other gods, which thou hast
&gt;not known, and let us serve them; Thou shalt not hearken unto the words
&gt;of that prophet, or that dreamer of dreams: for the LORD your God proveth
&gt;you, to know whether ye love the LORD your God with all your heart and
&gt;with all your soul. Ye shall walk after the LORD your God, and fear him,
&gt;and keep his commandments, and obey his voice, and ye shall serve him,
&gt;and cleave unto him. Deut 13:1-4
&gt; 
&gt; 
&gt;HAVE ANY OF ELLEN WHITE'S PROPHECIES COME TRUE?
&gt;-----------------------------------------------
&gt;By that I assume you mean her predictions of future events. Well yes,
&gt;as a matter of fact, most of them have come true (those that haven't
&gt;are either in the process of happening right now, or are yet future.)
&gt;     One example which I found very striking was this: A few years back,
&gt;I had just bought a book about Ellen White and the gift of prophecy, and
&gt;was reading its first chapter in my room.
&gt;     Apparently, Mrs White had said in 1902: "Not long hence, these
&gt;cities will suffer under the judgements of God. San Francisco and
&gt;Oakland are becoming as Sodom and Gomorrah, and the Lord will visit
&gt;them in wrath." - Manuscript 114, 1902. And again, in 1906, she said:
&gt;"I am bidden to declare the message that cities full of transgression,
&gt;and sinful in the extreme, will be destroyed by earthquakes, by fire,
&gt;by flood. All the world will be warned that there is a God who will
&gt;display His authority." - Manuscript 35, 1906. And just two days
&gt;BEFORE the great San Francisco earthquake and fire of April 18, 1906
&gt;she was shown this in a dream:
&gt; 
&gt;"..there passed before me a most wonderful representation. During a
&gt;vision of the night, I stood on an eminence, from which I could see
&gt;houses shaken like a reed in the wind. Buildings, great and small,
&gt;were falling to the ground. Pleasure resorts, theaters, hotels, and
&gt;the homes of the wealthy were shaken and shattered. Many lives were
&gt;blotted out of existence, and the air was filled with the shrieks of
&gt;the injured and the terrified.
&gt;     "The destroying angels of God were at work. One touch, and
&gt;buildings so thoroughly constructed that men regarded them as secure
&gt;against every danger, quickly became heaps of rubbish. There was no
&gt;assurance of safety in any place. I did not feel in any special peril,
&gt;but the awfulness of the scenes that passed before me I cannot find
&gt;words to describe. It seemed that the forbearance of God was exhausted,
&gt;and that the judgment day had come.
&gt;     "The angel that stood by my side then instructed me that but few
&gt;have any conception of the wickedness existing in our world to-day, and
&gt;especially the wickedness in the large cities. He declared that the Lord
&gt;has appointed a time when He will visit transgressors in wrath for
&gt;persistent disregard of His law.
&gt;     "Terrible as was the representation that passed before me, that
&gt;which impressed itself most vividly upon my mind was the instruction
&gt;given me in connection with it. The angel that stood by my side declared
&gt;that God's supreme rulership, and the sacredness of His law, must be
&gt;revealed to those who persistently refuse to render obedience to the
&gt;King of kings. Those who choose to remain disloyal, must be visited in
&gt;mercy with judgments, in order that, if possible, they may be aroused
&gt;to a realization of the sinfulness of their course."
&gt; 
&gt;"Awakening from this vision, she turned on the light. It was 1:00 a.m.
&gt;on Monday April 16, 1906. Four years earlier in 1902, she had first
&gt;predicted the destruction of San Francisco. Within 53 hours, it was
&gt;to take place." The book want on to say that: "490 city blocks were
&gt;destroyed; 256000 were left homeless. Mercifully only 498 died. Property
&gt;was destroyed at the rate of $1000000 every 10 minutes by the earthquake
&gt;and the fire which followed it which burned at times with blast-furnace
&gt;heat, ranging up to 2000F.  Yet she later warned of still more
&gt;destruction in the future upon these and other wicked cities.
&gt;     "The light given to me is that the wickedness in the cities of
&gt;San Francisco and Oakland is beyond all imagination. God's wrath is
&gt;upon many of the inhabitants of these cities." - Manuscript 25, 1908
&gt;     "These things make me feel very solemn, because I know that the
&gt;judgement day is right upon us. The judgements that have already come
&gt;are a warning, but not the finishing, of the punishment that will come
&gt;on wicked cities." - letter 154, 1906.
&gt;     "I feel sure that San Francisco and Oakland will again be visited
&gt;with the judgements of God" - Letter 2, 1909.
&gt;     Seismology was yet in its infancy. But warnings given then are
&gt;recognised today by leading scientists as facts to be fulfilled again
&gt;along the San Andreas Fault.
&gt;     When a prophet speaks, it comes to pass.
&gt; 
&gt;     The reason I found this so striking was that just as I was reading
&gt;this, the program on the BBC world service radio, which was playing in
&gt;my room, was interrupted for a newsflash. It said that quite a bad
&gt;earthquake had just hit San Francisco and Oakland. Later, more details
&gt;about the damage and the double-tier highway bridge collapsing came in.
&gt;When you read about a prophecy and it comes true just as you read it, it
&gt;is very striking! Anyway, after that one, I think there have been a few
&gt;other earthquakes around that region, but according to scientists, the
&gt;big one is yet to strike.
&gt; 
&gt;     There are numerous other predictions which have come true, and some
&gt;which are happening right now, if you want to know more about them, I
&gt;could recommend you some books about it. Appart from this Ellen White
&gt;wrote very widely on topics such as health, family life, etc. She has
&gt;written some very good books on the Christian Life and the life of Jesus
&gt;too. They give you good insights into the bible and make inspiring
&gt;devotional reading too.
&gt; 
&gt;     God bless,
&gt;               Beng Yong Tang, Singapore.
&gt;
</pre>
