[Please get Ruben's name and all other names out of the subject<br>
line, try to focus on the issues.  Thanks, SCT]<br>
Ruben writes:<br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; Salvation is by faith alone, however faith = trust and obey. So that</i><br>
<i>&gt; the saving faith is that faith that obeys. For this reason the translation</i><br>
<i>&gt; of Rev 22:14 is correct because it exemplifies that type of faith necessary</i><br>
<i>&gt; for salvation. For this very reason Rev 22:14 (KJV style) is unpopular</i><br>
<i>&gt; with evangelicals.</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; Ruben.</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
I think it may clarify this issue by quoting Elen White's definition<br>
of faith:  <br>
<p>
"What is faith? . . . It is an assent of the understanding to God's<br>
words which binds the heart in willing consecration and service to<br>
God, . . . Faith is rendering to God the intellectual powers,<br>
abandonment of the mind and will to God, and making Christ the only<br>
door to enter into the kingdom of heaven."  --Faith and Works, p. 25<br>
<p>
Thus, obedience is not a part of faith.  But one who has the kind of<br>
faith Ellen White is refering to will obey.<br>
<p>
