<p>
No, but it definitely takes work to build a relationship with anyone, including<br>
God.  I define work as the putting forth of effort or the expenditure of energy.<br>
The difference here is working at a relationship, not working at salvation. The<br>
salvation part is a free gift to all who would accept Christ and start a<br>
relationship with Him.  As long as I demonstrate my acceptance by maintaining<br>
the relationship, I will continue to be assured of retaining my free gift of<br>
salvation.<br>
<p>
By the way, what was out of context?...your comments or mine?  I believe my<br>
comments were relavent and in the context of the subject line.<br>
