[From Tony Dyson]<br>
I have just realized that I have an opportunity to agree with Ruben on<br>
something, so I thought I'd better take it up  :)<br>
<p>
Ruben was using some humour (whoops - humor for all you American-speakers)<br>
in his post to you, Bruce, so don't get too stirred up. Although I was<br>
reminded of the old adage that "many a true word is spoken in jest".<br>
<p>
Now I'm no believer in perfectionism, but this one point struck me: <br>
perhaps "working on a relationship" also entails working on removing<br>
obstacles to that relationship. In that context, trying ones best to<br>
live the way God would have one live is indeed part of working on<br>
building a relationship with him. <br>
<p>
Let's not be too quick to use the label "legalist" or the phrase<br>
"salvation by works" whenever someone mentions lifestyle, standards<br>
or the ten commandments.<br>
<p>
Tony<br>
