<title>Feb_1993: Call for SDAnet board</title>
<h1>Call for SDAnet board</h1>
Steven Timm (<i>st0o+@andrew.cmu.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Tue,  9 Feb 1993 23:02:36 -0500 (EST)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#92">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#92">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#92">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#92">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0093.html">Steven Timm: "EC and Sunday Law"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0091.html">Steven Timm: "Works of confusion"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
As the happy day of completing my doctoral program and receiving a Ph.D<br>
draws nearer (probably late '93), I am forced to consider some of the <br>
eventualities that may happen after that time.<br>
<p>
1)  Getting no job and losing net access<br>
<p>
2)  Getting a job out of the country (Jamaica, for instance) and losing <br>
    net access.<br>
<p>
3)  Getting a job at a government institution where running mailing lists<br>
    like this (or even receiving them) is banned.<br>
<p>
4)  In any case, losing my account at andrew.cmu.edu and having to move<br>
    the list elsewhere, sometime during 1994.<br>
<p>
Some of the original people who were on SDAnet when it started have <br>
provided advice to me in an unofficial capacity from time to time, <br>
and I have appreciated this.  When I have been unfair to some person or<br>
group, I hear about it.<br>
<p>
I feel that now is the time to form a more official board to ensure<br>
both accountability and survivability of SDAnet.  The types of people<br>
I would like to see serve on this board should have at least one of the<br>
following attributes:<br>
<p>
1)  A long term job, likely to maintain position and personal net access<br>
    for some length of time<br>
<p>
2)  Influence in the computing dept. of an SDA institution to arrange a<br>
    backup host machine for SDAnet if necessary, and/or an account for <br>
    the moderator.<br>
<p>
3)  Willingness to serve as backup moderator or replacement moderator <br>
    if necessary<br>
<p>
4)  Technical knowledge of networking and mailing list software<br>
<p>
5)  An interest in seeing SDAnet continue for the long term.<br>
<p>
<p>
If you meet any one of the five requirements above, and would like <br>
to serve on the board, please let me know.  If there are more than five<br>
people that apply for the board, we will put the names out on the net<br>
and let everyone vote.<br>
<p>
Steve Timm<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
