<!-- body="start" -->
<i>&gt; In this month's Liberty magazine there is an article about how the</i><br>
<i>&gt; European Community, through the European Parliament, is adopting a</i><br>
<i>&gt; resolution designating Sunday as the uniform day of rest throughout</i><br>
<i>&gt; the EC.  I can provide more details if needed.</i><br>
<p>
It would be interesting to know if this is actually going to happen or<br>
simply was proposed.  This is an instance of the "social dimension"<br>
aspect of the EC, which is the most controversial part and which has<br>
gotten a lot of bad publicity the last few years as part of the<br>
Maastricht Treaty debate.  Some countries, e.g. Britain, are going the<br>
other direction, with High Street shops opening on Sunday and ignoring<br>
the exhortations of the Church of England.<br>
<p>
Glen McCluskey<br>
glenm@usl.com<br>
