<title>Feb_1993: EC and Daniel 2 prophecy</title>
<h1>EC and Daniel 2 prophecy</h1>
Bruce Holm (<i>bruceh@wv.mentorg.com</i>)<br>
<i>Wed, 10 Feb 93 15:26:21 -0800</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#103">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#103">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#103">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#103">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0104.html">Fred Christiansen: "Re: EGW quote"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0102.html">Ruben Gonzalez: "Bruce,, commandment keeping and just. by faith"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
Hi all,<br>
<p>
Steve's discussion of the EC and Sunday Laws reminds me of something<br>
that I'd like to hear input on from others.  Does the prophecy of Dan. 2<br>
(large man image of various metal types) and particularly the time in which<br>
we live represented by the feet of the image apply to the EC?  In other<br>
words, does the general SDA viewpoint that the feet and toes of part iron<br>
and part clay that don't mix apply to the EC?  If so, then the EC will either<br>
never happen or will fail shortly after joining.  This of course would<br>
represent a tremendous waste of money trying to pull off something prophecied<br>
to never happen.<br>
<p>
Our church is currently holding a Daniel seminar and just covered Dan. 2.<br>
The person leading out pointed out that history records 7 times where<br>
attempts to conquor and politically combine Europe have failed, including<br>
attempts by Charlemain, Napolean, Kaiser, Hitler, etc.  But these were<br>
attempts at military conquoring and would have been rulerships by one<br>
person.  The EC is a little different but having one monitary system, etc,<br>
does come pretty close in my mind.<br>
<p>
What do you all think?<br>
<p>
--Bruce<br>
<pre>
-- 
Bruce G. Holm               503-685-1350      email:  bruceh@wv.mentorg.com
Mentor Graphics Corp.       503-685-7000
8005 SW Boeckman Rd.
Wilsonville, OR 97070-7777     Disclaimer:  Opinions expressed are my own!
</pre>
<!-- body="end" -->
