<title>Feb_1993: Re: EGW quote</title>
<h1>Re: EGW quote</h1>
Fred Christiansen (<i>fredch@phx.mcd.mot.com</i>)<br>
<i>Wed, 10 Feb 93 10:52:42 MST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#104">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#104">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#104">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#104">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0105.html">Ruben Gonzalez: "Re: Inspiration: questions"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0103.html">Bruce Holm: "EC and Daniel 2 prophecy"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
<i>&gt; "What is faith? . . . It is an assent of the understanding to God's</i><br>
<i>&gt; words which binds the heart in willing consecration and service to</i><br>
<i>&gt; God, . . . &gt;&gt;&gt; Faith is rendering to God the intellectual powers,</i><br>
<i>&gt; abandonment of the mind and will to God, &lt;&lt;&lt; and making Christ the only</i><br>
<i>&gt; door to enter into the kingdom of heaven."  --Faith and Works, p. 25</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; Thus, obedience is not a part of faith.  But one who has the kind of</i><br>
<i>&gt; faith Ellen White is refering to will obey.</i><br>
<p>
Excellent quote; for me, esp what I put in &gt;&gt;&gt; .. &lt;&lt;&lt;.  IMHO, sanctification<br>
is the process by which the Holy Spirit leads us into accepting the Lordship<br>
of Christ in every nook and cranny of our "intellectual powers", our mind,<br>
will, and emotions (cf 2 Chr 16:9a).  "Abandonment" is apt.  And to trust Him<br>
that far we need to know Him intimately (the relationship part).<br>
<p>
The motive for obedience?  Love.  Jn 14:15, Rom 5:5, 1 Jn 4:19.<br>
The means?  Grace (= the desire and the power).  Phi 2:13.<br>
<pre>
-- 
Fred Christiansen, Motorola, 2900 S Diablo Way, Tempe, AZ 85282  "Canajun, eh?"
fredch@phx.mcd.mot.com  ||  uunet!phx.mcd.mot.com!fredch  ||  +1 602-438-3464
  ".. I have set before you Life and Death, blessing and cursing;  therefore
      choose Life, that both you and your children may live"  Deut 30:19
</pre>
