<title>Feb_1993: EC and Daniel 2 prophecy</title>
<h1>EC and Daniel 2 prophecy</h1>
Ruben Gonzalez (<i>ruben@ee.uts.edu.au</i>)<br>
<i>Thu, 11 Feb 93 15:51:21 EST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#108">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#108">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#108">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#108">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0109.html">Steven Timm: "Things for the board to help with"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0107.html">PHTH1@cc.newcastle.edu.au: "Iron and clay"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
Hi all,<br>
<p>
<p>
In my study of EGWs position on this issue I found that EGW does not<br>
restrict the feet and toes to the nations of Europe. Instead she uses<br>
the phrase "kingdoms of this world" when refering to them. The notion<br>
that they refer specifically to the European powers was most popular<br>
with other pioneers such as Uriah Smith. Like wise the concept that<br>
Europe would never unite is slightly misleading because under the Holy<br>
Roman Empire it was effectively united. Whether or not the EC will unite<br>
is hard to say but then Rev does say that the kings of the earth unite with<br>
the Dragon.<br>
<p>
I prefer to think that Dan 2 refers to the entire world and not just one<br>
small segment of it.<br>
<p>
Ruben.<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
