<title>Feb_1993: Symposium on networking in the SDA church</title>
<h1>Symposium on networking in the SDA church</h1>
Steven Timm (<i>st0o+@andrew.cmu.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Wed, 10 Feb 1993 23:26:56 -0500 (EST)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#110">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#110">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#110">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#110">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0111.html">Marcus Stringer: "RE: EC and Daniel 2 prophecy"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0109.html">Steven Timm: "Things for the board to help with"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
<li> <b>Next in thread:</b> <a href="0143.html">Ausberto Castro V.: "Re:  Symposium on networking in the SDA church"</a>
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
For some time I have wondered whether or not it would be feasible to <br>
hold a symposium on the benefits and potential benefits of electronic<br>
networking to the SDA church.  Some ideas that such a symposium would <br>
cover are:<br>
<p>
The network as a witnessing tool<br>
The network as a communication tool<br>
The network as a means of sharing resources<br>
The network as an education aid<br>
<p>
<p>
If you have ideas on other topics that a symposium should cover,<br>
please share them.  Also share your thoughts on whether such a symposium<br>
should be electronic or would actually bring everybody together into <br>
one place.<br>
<p>
Steve Timm<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
<ul>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0111.html">Marcus Stringer: "RE: EC and Daniel 2 prophecy"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0109.html">Steven Timm: "Things for the board to help with"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
<li> <b>Next in thread:</b> <a href="0143.html">Ausberto Castro V.: "Re:  Symposium on networking in the SDA church"</a>
